\fs32 \cf2 Diagnosed filter logic mismatch between displayed and source writers\
\
The bug is conceptual, not just code. The filter checks 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 r.srcs
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  \'97 all writers who ever recommended a restaurant \'97 but the card displays only one writer's name and quote. So El Rinconcillo passes the Lauren Aloise filter because she's in its 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 srcs
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 , but the card shows Claudia Campos as the credited writer. From the user's perspective, that's wrong.\
The fix: filter on 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 r.writer
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  \'97 the writer actually credited on the card \'97 not 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 r.srcs
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 . I also need to normalise two mismatches in the data where 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 r.writer
