\fs28 \cf4 Connecting to visualize...
\fs32 \cf2 \
The fix was a conceptual one, not just a code bug. Here's the clear explanation:\
The problem: Each restaurant has a 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 srcs
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  array listing every writer who recommended it, but the card only displays one writer's name and quote. The filter was checking 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 r.srcs
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  \'97 so clicking Lauren Aloise would show El Rinconcillo (she's in its srcs list) but the card credits Claudia Campos. From your perspective, that's a wrong result.\
The fix: The filter now matches against 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 r.writer
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  \'97 the writer actually credited on the card \'97 not 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 r.srcs
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 . Clicking Lauren Aloise now shows exactly and only her 4 restaurants, each with her name on the attribution line.\
The data also has two fields now:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls22\ilvl0
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
writer
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  \'97 the normalised filter key (exactly matches button labels)\
\ls22\ilvl0
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
writerDisplay
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  \'97 the full display name shown on the card (e.g. "Tourist to Local team", "ExactChange Sevilla", "Cristina Fern\'e1ndez Gonz\'e1lez")\
