\fs32 \cf2 Acknowledged suboptimal search year choice; flagged staleness concern\
\
Honestly, it was a mistake on my part. The current date is March 2026, so anchoring both searches to "2024" likely caused me to miss more recent material \'97 the Gambero Rosso Lombardia 2025 guide, for instance, which I ended up citing anyway but could easily have missed.\
The better approach would have been either:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls28\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
No year at all \'97 let the search engine surface the most recent results naturally\
\ls28\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
2025 or 2026 \'97 explicitly pull the most current guides and rankings\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Specifying "2024" is a habit that makes sense when you're near that year, but in 2026 it's counterproductive \'97 it biases results toward older material and may filter out the freshest editions of annual guides like Gambero Rosso, Puntarella Rossa's rankings, or updated articles from Conosco un posto.\
Worth noting for the search design going forward: for a product like LocalBite where recency matters (restaurants close, quality changes, new places open), the searches should either omit the year entirely or use the current year. I'll apply that correction in future city runs.\
