\fs32 \cf2 Verdict\
2026 wins, but narrowly. The meaningful difference is two results:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls29\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Time Out Milan's full best-restaurants guide (January 2026) surfaced in the 2026 search but not the no-year search, which only returned the narrower "eat like a local" piece. The full guide contains more restaurant recommendations and has the editorial note "2026 update" \'97 this is genuinely newer information.\
\ls29\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Roam & Thrive's 2026 roundup surfaced in the 2026 search and introduced Stendhal Brera \'97 a Milanese-cuisine restaurant not in any of the other sources \'97 and with a recent first-person write-up. That's a real new discovery.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Against that, the no-year search surfaced La Cucina Italiana (2019) and Fine Dining Lovers (2021) \'97 older material that could easily include restaurants that have changed or closed. The 2026 search mostly suppressed those in favour of more current content.\
The practical recommendation for LocalBite: use the current year in searches. It consistently pulls more recent source editions and introduces genuinely new restaurant discoveries, without meaningfully losing good sources that are already captured. The only risk is occasionally surfacing something titled "2026" that's a thin aggregator \'97 but those are easy to spot and discard.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
