\fs32 \cf2 Audited source articles and included all verified restaurants comprehensively\
\
Honestly: I included almost every restaurant named in every article, with minimal additional filtering of my own. The only exclusion was Giannasi from the Curious Appetite list \'97 a takeaway chicken and timballo counter that clearly wasn't a sit-down Milanese restaurant in the spirit of the widget.\
Beyond that one obvious case, the selection was essentially "everything the writers named, de-duplicated across sources." I didn't apply any additional editorial judgment \'97 no quality threshold, no rating cutoff, no attempt to pick the best five from each article.\
Which means the curation in this widget is almost entirely the writers' curation, not mine. I functioned more as an aggregator and cross-referencer than as an editor. The value I added was:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls30\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Fetching the actual pages to confirm each restaurant is named there\
\ls30\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Tracking which restaurants appear in multiple sources (the overlap signal)\
\ls30\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Attaching Google ratings and place data\
\ls30\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Organising it into a filterable interface\
