\cf2 What I didn't do \'97 and what a real LocalBite product probably should do \'97 is apply a secondary editorial pass: asking whether a restaurant that appears in only one source, from 2024, with a 4.1 Google rating is genuinely worth including alongside a restaurant that five sources across two languages agree on. That judgment was left entirely to the original writers.\
So the honest summary is: the verified-first approach solved the fabrication problem, but it didn't introduce any editorial curation beyond what the source writers already exercised. Whether that's the right design for LocalBite \'97 or whether there should be a quality or recency threshold before a restaurant makes the list \'97 is a product decision you'd still need to make.\
