\fs28 \cf6 Recalled distinction between data retrieval classification terms\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 Recalled distinction between data retrieval classification terms\
\
A meaningful one, and worth being precise about.\
Fully fetched means I called the 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 web_fetch
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  tool on the actual URL and read the full article text in this conversation. I can see every restaurant name on the page. The Spanish Sabores article is a good example \'97 I fetched it and got the complete list of 24 named restaurants, their addresses, what to order, and the surrounding context. The attribution is as close to certain as it can be.\
Search-confirmed means I ran a web search targeting the site (e.g. 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 site:devourtours.com best restaurants seville
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 ) and the search results returned snippets \'97 typically the page title, a short excerpt, and a list of restaurant names visible in the preview text. I didn't read the full article; I inferred the restaurant list from what appeared in the search snippet. The snippet showed enough names to confirm they're there, but I may have missed restaurants that didn't appear in the preview, and I can't guarantee I correctly understood the context around each name.\
So the risk profile is different. A fully fetched article gives me high confidence: I read what the writer said about each place and can confirm the restaurant is genuinely named as a recommendation. A search-confirmed article gives me moderate confidence: I can see the name is associated with that publication, but I haven't verified the full list, the surrounding language, or whether the mention is a recommendation versus a passing reference or a warning to avoid.\
For LocalBite's standards, search-confirmation is probably not sufficient. Every source article should be fully fetched before any restaurant from it makes the list. In the Seville rebuild I fetched two and search-confirmed three, which means roughly half the dataset is built on weaker evidence than it should be. The three unverified sources \'97 Devour Tours, Sevilla Secreta, and Gu\'eda Repsol \'97 should each be fully fetched before their restaurants are treated as verified.\
