Yes, several things. Trying to be as complete as I can here:\
Gu\'eda Repsol bars 4\'9615 are still only search-confirmed, not fully fetched. The article is JavaScript-rendered and only bars 1\'963 (Plato Plat\'f3, La Atrayana, Velout\'e9) were confirmed from the fetched text. Becerrita and Palo Cortao came from search snippets \'97 the same intermediate status I criticised in the previous version. I should have flagged this explicitly rather than presenting all three Gu\'eda Repsol additions as equivalent.\
Sevilla Secreta has multiple articles. I fetched the 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 /tapas/
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  guide, which covers 32 tapas across many bars. But Sevilla Secreta also has a separate bares and restaurants article. When I removed attributions like Bodega Santa Cruz and Casa Morales from Sevilla Secreta, I only confirmed they're not in that tapas article \'97 they may genuinely appear in a different Sevilla Secreta article I haven't fetched. The removal was correct for this specific URL but may be wrong at the source level.\
The card quotes are my paraphrases, not the writers' words. When the widget says "Lauren Aloise says..." or "Claudia writes...", that's my synthesis of what I read, not a direct quote. A reader clicking through to the original article might find the phrasing or emphasis differs from what I presented.\
Devour Tours has a named writer I didn't surface. The article was written by Emma Fajcz. LocalBite's entire premise is writer-attributed recommendations, but the Devour Tours cards say "Devour Tours editorial" rather than naming the actual author. This is a gap in the product logic.\
Article recency varies significantly. The Sevilla Secreta tapas article was last updated in August 2023. The Gu\'eda Repsol article in November 2023. Restaurants close, change chefs, and decline in quality. I haven't flagged article dates on any card, so a reader has no way to assess how stale a recommendation might be.\
Chifa's missing map listing is more significant than I indicated. I noted it with a 
\f1 \uc0\u9888 
\f0  symbol, but the honest implication is that a restaurant which can't be confirmed on Google Maps in 2026 may simply have closed. I treated this as a minor caveat when it probably warrants excluding the entry entirely until confirmed open.\
The "local writer" badge is applied inconsistently. I gave it to Claudia Campos and the Spanish publications, but Devour Tours is a Spain-based food tour company whose writers have deep local expertise. And Spanish Sabores is written by Lauren Aloise, who lived in Seville for years and co-founded the city's food tours. The badge is doing less meaningful work than it implies.\
Source selection itself is unexamined. I chose these five sources, but there are many other Seville food publications \'97 Gu\'eda Hedonista, El Comidista, ABC Sevilla's food section, and others \'97 that I haven't included. The widget presents itself as a curated picture of what food writers recommend, but it's really a curated picture of what these five writers recommend. That's a meaningful difference for a product that claims to surface local editorial opinion.\
The "both pools" signal conflates independent agreement with corroboration. When four sources all name El Rinconcillo, that looks like strong independent agreement. But it's possible that three of those sources were drawing on the same prior source, or that El Rinconcillo is so famous that any Seville food guide mentions it regardless of independent assessment. Cross-source confirmation is weaker evidence than it appears.\
The most actionable of these for the actual LocalBite product: article dates should appear on every card, and the Gu\'eda Repsol bars 4\'9615 need to be properly fetched before they can be treated as verified.\
