\fs32 \cf2 Synthesized search methodology prioritizing publications over restaurants\
\
Based on everything learned, here's my honest assessment \'97 organised by what the searches are actually trying to accomplish, since that's what determines whether a search term is useful.\
\
The core insight first\
The search is not the research. Searches should be used only to find article URLs that can then be fetched and read in full. The mistake throughout the Seville sessions was treating search results as a substitute for reading the source \'97 using snippets to infer restaurant lists rather than fetching the page. So the quality of the search terms matters less than the discipline of always fetching what you find.\
\
Phase 1: Finding relevant publications\
The goal here is to identify which writers and publications cover this city well \'97 before thinking about any specific restaurants.\
Good patterns:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls39\ilvl0
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
best food writers [city] local guide [year]
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 \
\ls39\ilvl0
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
mejores gu\'edas gastron\'f3micas [ciudad] locales [year]
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  (for Spanish cities)\
\ls39\ilvl0
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
food blog [city] local recommendations writer
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 \
\ls39\ilvl0
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
who writes about food in [city]
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  \'97 surprisingly useful for surfacing individual bylines\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Avoid:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls40\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Searching for specific restaurants at this stage \'97 it anchors you to restaurants before you've found the writers\
\ls40\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Using the 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 site:
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  operator \'97 it artificially narrows results and I was wrong to use it repeatedly\
\ls40\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Including years older than current \'97 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 2024
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  in March 2026 is stale; use current year or none\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
Phase 2: Finding specific articles from identified publications\
Once you have a publication name (e.g. Sevilla Secreta, Spanish Sabores), the goal is to find the specific article URL \'97 not to extract restaurants from the snippet.\
Good patterns:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls41\ilvl0
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
[publication name] [city] tapas restaurants guide [year]
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 \
\ls41\ilvl0
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
[publication name] donde comer [ciudad] bares recomendados
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  (Spanish)\
\ls41\ilvl0
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
[writer name] [city] restaurants recommendations
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Then immediately fetch the URL returned. Do not read the snippet as a source.\
Avoid:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls42\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Searches like 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 site:sevillasecreta.co mejores bares tapas Sevilla
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  \'97 the 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 site:
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  operator often returns a list of results rather than a single definitive article, making it tempting to cherry-pick snippets instead of reading one complete piece\
\ls42\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Searching for 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 [restaurant name] [publication name]
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  \'97 this is the backwards approach that caused the fabrication problem; it starts from a restaurant and tries to find a source for it, rather than starting from a source and extracting restaurants from it\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
Phase 3: Verifying you have the right article before fetching\
One intermediate step worth adding: before fetching, confirm the URL looks like a genuine editorial article and not a directory, aggregator, or sponsored content page. Signs to watch for:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls43\ilvl0
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
/blog/
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 , 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 /guide/
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 , 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 /recomendaciones/
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 , 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 /gastronomia/
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  in the URL path \'97 good\
\ls43\ilvl0
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
/listings/
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 , 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 /sponsored/
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 , 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 /partner/
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  \'97 treat with caution\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls43\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
A writer byline visible in the snippet \'97 good\
\ls43\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
No byline, just a publication name \'97 still worth fetching, but note it\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
Phase 4: Confirming completeness after fetching\
After fetching an article, a search can be useful to check whether you've missed something:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls44\ilvl0
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
[publication name] [city] restaurants [year] -[article you already have]
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  \'97 to see if there are other articles from the same source worth fetching\
\ls44\ilvl0
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
[city] food guide [language] local writers [year]
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  \'97 to check whether there are relevant publications you haven't found yet\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
What I would not bother searching for at all\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls45\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Individual restaurant names at any point before the widget-building stage\
\ls45\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
"Best restaurants [city]" without a publication or writer name \'97 this surfaces aggregators and SEO content, not genuine food writing\
\ls45\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Anything with quotes around multi-word phrases \'97 this over-constrains results and I misused it repeatedly in Session 3\
\ls45\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Any query designed to confirm a source-restaurant pairing you already have in mind \'97 this is the cognitive trap that produced fabricated attributions\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
The honest meta-point\
The most reliable output doesn't primarily depend on better search terms. It depends on a clear process: find writers 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  fetch their articles 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  extract what's explicitly named 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  build. The searches are just URL-finding tools in that process. Better search terms used in the wrong process (search 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  infer 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  build) will still produce unreliable output. The discipline of fetching and reading is what matters most.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \
