\cf2 Yes, exactly right. The commonality is that both put a human in the quality gate before anything reaches the user.\
In Interpretation 3 the human is present during the research process \'97 approving sources, confirming extractions, catching errors as they happen. In Interpretation 4 the human has already done that work offline, and the result is a finished, trusted city pack that gets published.\
You could think of Interpretation 3 as the production process and Interpretation 4 as the output. They're not competing approaches \'97 Interpretation 3 is how you build the city packs that Interpretation 4 serves to users. The tool you'd build for Interpretation 3 (the human-guided pipeline) is essentially the internal editorial tool that produces the data behind Interpretation 4 (the curated library).\
This is actually a clean product architecture:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls56\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Internal tool \'97 Interpretation 3. A researcher uses the human-in-the-loop pipeline to build and verify a city pack. The three-phase approach, fetch-before-extract, source confirmation \'97 all of that runs here, with a human reviewing each step.\
\ls56\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Public product \'97 Interpretation 4. Users browse and filter the verified city packs produced by the internal tool. Fast, trusted, no automation risk touching what users see.\
\ls56\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Long-term automation \'97 Interpretation 2. As the prompt becomes proven reliable against the packs already built manually, you gradually automate parts of the internal tool, using the existing verified packs as a quality benchmark to test against.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The three interpretations then form a natural roadmap rather than alternatives you have to choose between.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
