\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf2 The risks specific to Interpretation 3\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 Researcher fatigue \'97 If the approval steps are too granular, the human-in-the-loop becomes more burden than benefit. The UI needs to make approvals fast \'97 one click per source, not a form to fill in. The goal is that a researcher can produce a city pack in 30\'9645 minutes, not 3 hours.\
Inconsistent human decisions \'97 Two different researchers might make different calls about the same source. For a single-researcher prototype this doesn't matter, but for a team it means you need lightweight editorial guidelines alongside the tool.\
Jina reliability \'97 Jina is a third-party service. It's reliable for most pages but has the same JS-rendering and paywall limitations we encountered. The tool needs to handle fetch failures gracefully and show the researcher a clear message when a page couldn't be read rather than silently continuing.\
Scope creep in the UI \'97 A step-by-step wizard is easy to over-engineer. The prototype should be functional, not beautiful. Plain HTML with minimal styling is fine for week 1\'963. Resist the temptation to polish the UI before the pipeline is proven.\
