\fs32 \cf2 Diagnosed CORS limitations and pivoted toward server-side solution\
\
The "Load failed" error is a CORS problem \'97 browsers block direct calls to 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 api.anthropic.com
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  because the API is designed for server-side use, not browser-based requests. The widget runs in a sandboxed iframe which makes this worse. The Jina fetch calls to 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 r.jina.ai
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  are likely also blocked for the same reason.\
This is a fundamental limitation of the browser widget approach, not something fixable with a code tweak. The pipeline needs to run server-side.\
The right environment for this is Claude Code.\
Claude Code runs in your terminal, not a browser \'97 so it can make API calls to Anthropic directly, fetch URLs via Jina, and write the JSON output to your filesystem, none of which hit CORS restrictions.\
The build would look like this: a single Node.js or Python script that runs in your terminal, prompts you at each step (approve/reject sources, review extracted restaurants), and writes the final JSON pack to a file. The interactive approval happens in the terminal rather than a browser UI, which is less polished but fully functional for a prototype.\
