\fs28 \cf10 \cb9 I am building a tool called LocalBite that finds restaurant recommendations from local food writers. Please help me research Valencia, Spain using a human-in-the-loop pipeline. Here is exactly what I need you to do:\
\
PHASE 1 \'97 Find sources\
Search the web for 5-8 credible local food writers and publications that have written restaurant or tapas guides for Valencia, Spain. Prefer named authors, local bloggers, and established food publications. Avoid TripAdvisor, Yelp, and generic travel blogs. Do NOT name any restaurants yet. Show me the list with publication name, writer name, URL, and one sentence on why it is credible. Wait for me to approve which sources to include before proceeding.\
\
PHASE 2 \'97 Fetch and extract\
For each source I approve, fetch the article using https://r.jina.ai/ prepended to the URL. Read the fetched text carefully. Extract ONLY restaurants that are explicitly named in the article text. Do not use your training knowledge to add restaurants not mentioned in the text. For each restaurant show me the name, neighbourhood, a signature dish if mentioned, and a one-sentence paraphrase of what the writer says. Show me the results one source at a time and wait for me to confirm before moving to the next source. Let me remove any entries that look wrong.\
\
PHASE 3 \'97 Assemble and export\
Once all sources are processed, combine the results into a single list. If the same restaurant appears in both an English source and a Spanish source, mark it as both-pool. Sort with both-pool entries first, then by number of sources. Show me the final list with counts. Then write the complete results to a file called localbite-valencia-spain.json in my current directory using this structure:\
\
\{\
  "city": "Valencia",\
  "country": "Spain", \
  "city_slug": "valencia-spain",\
  "built": "[today's date]",\
  "pipeline": "localbite-human-in-loop-v1",\
  "sources": [array of approved sources with id, publication, writer, url, language],\
  "restaurants": [array with name, neighbourhood, price_level, signature_dish, quote, language_pool, source_count, sources array]\
\}\
\
Important rules:\
- Never include a restaurant unless it was explicitly named in a fetched article\
- If a fetch fails or returns very little content, skip that source and tell me\
- Fetch quality matters \'97 tell me how many characters were returned for each fetch\
- Wait for my approval at each stage before proceeding\
\
Please start with Phase 1 now.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

