\cf2 Good question \'97 and honestly, you may not need to.\
The two files serve different purposes and that's actually a feature not a problem:\
localbite-valencia-spain.json (75 restaurants) \'97 built from any credible source regardless of date. Includes older articles from Hello Valencia and others. Broader coverage but some sources may be stale.\
localbite-valencia-2025-2026.json (62 restaurants) \'97 built exclusively from 2025-2026 sources. Tighter, more current, better quality quotes and dish descriptions throughout.\
The case for merging would be to get maximum coverage \'97 restaurants that appear in older sources but not newer ones would be captured. But there's a reasonable case against merging too: the 2025-2026 file is cleaner and more trustworthy, and mixing it with older sources muddies the recency guarantee.\
My honest recommendation is to treat the 2025-2026 file as your canonical Valencia pack going forward and set the older file aside as an archive. If you later want to check whether a restaurant from the older file deserves to be added to the canonical pack, you could do that selectively rather than doing a bulk merge.\
