\fs28 \cf10 \cb9 SOURCE CONCENTRATION CAP \'97 apply during Phase 3 assembly:\
No single source may contribute more than 30% of the final restaurant count.\
\
Apply this rule as follows:\
1. After assembling all entries, count the total restaurants in the table (Tier A + Tier B, before recommended removals)\
2. Calculate 30% of that total \'97 this is the cap for any single source\
3. If any single source exceeds the cap in single-source-only entries (i.e. entries where that source is the only one), rank those single-source entries by confidence within that source \'97 prioritise entries with: both a signature dish AND a named chef or physical description, then entries with one of those, then entries with neither\
4. Auto-reject the lowest-ranked single-source entries from that source until it falls within the 30% cap\
5. Report this in the AUTO-REJECTED section: "Source concentration cap applied: [source name] reduced from [X] to [Y] entries \'97 [Z] auto-rejected"\
\
Note: Tier A entries (multi-source or both-pool) are exempt from this cap \'97 it only applies to single-source Tier B entries from that publication.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \
The key design decisions in this wording:\
Only single-source entries count toward the cap \'97 if Time Out appears alongside another source in a Tier A entry, that doesn't count against Time Out's allocation. The cap is specifically about Time Out being the sole voice on an entry.\
Ranking by confidence before cutting \'97 rather than cutting arbitrarily, the weakest entries go first. This preserves the best Time Out material while reducing the tail of lower-quality entries.\
Transparent reporting \'97 the auto-rejected section will explicitly tell you the cap was applied and how many entries were cut, so you can audit it.\
Tier A exemption \'97 if Bar Super appears in both Time Out and The Infatuation, that's genuine confirmation and shouldn't be penalised just because Time Out is one of the sources.\
In the Barcelona run we just completed, Time Out had roughly 40 single-source entries out of 84 total \'97 about 48%. The cap would have reduced that to around 25 entries, cutting the 15 weakest Time Out-only picks automatically before the review table appeared.\
