STEP 1 \'97 Combine and deduplicate\
Merge all extracted restaurants into one list. If the same restaurant\
appears in multiple sources combine into one entry with all sources listed.\
Apply name normalisation from Phase 2 \'97 use the normalised name for the\
final entry. Report the total number of merge operations performed.\
\
STEP 2 \'97 Assign confidence tier to every entry\
\
TIER A \'97 Auto-approve (do not flag):\
- 2 or more sources, OR\
- Both-pool (appears in at least one EN source AND at least one ES or CA\
  source that is editorially independent \'97 sibling editions of the same\
  publication do not count as separate pools)\
Reasoning: independent confirmation makes these reliable without review.\
\
TIER B \'97 Review recommended:\
Primary source entries (local bloggers, local press, independent writers):\
- 1 source only, AND good fetch quality, AND quote contains at least one\
  specific detail (dish name, chef name, physical description, price,\
  or year)\
\
Secondary source entries (Time Out, Cond\'e9 Nast, Lonely Planet):\
- 1 source only, AND good fetch quality, AND quote contains at least TWO\
  specific details (e.g. dish name plus chef name, or dish name plus\
  physical description, or price plus year)\
- If only one specific detail: auto-reject to Tier C\
\
Reasoning: secondary sources require stronger evidence for single-source\
entries.\
\
TIER C \'97 Auto-reject (exclude before presenting table):\
- 1 source only AND fetch quality partial or failed\
- OR: quote is generic with no specific details\
- OR: secondary source single-source entry with fewer than two specific\
  details\
- OR: outside Barcelona city boundary\
Reasoning: data too weak to include.\
\
SOURCE CONCENTRATION CAP\
After assembling all entries:\
1. Count total restaurants (Tier A + Tier B combined)\
2. Calculate 30% of that total\
3. If any single source has more single-source-only Tier B entries than\
   that cap allows, rank its single-source entries by confidence:\
   - Highest: signature dish AND (named chef OR physical description)\
   - Middle: signature dish OR named chef OR physical description\
   - Lowest: year or price only\
4. Auto-reject the lowest-ranked entries from that source until it falls\
   within the cap\
5. Report this in the AUTO-REJECTED section\
