\fs32 \cf2 We added that instruction to prevent the output token limit crash. The logic was: fetching everything at once, then trying to write all extractions in a single response, was what hit the 32,000 token ceiling.\
However the fetch itself doesn't cause the token problem \'97 it's the extraction and writing that does. So we could safely allow parallel fetches as long as the extraction and writing still happens one source at a time. That would look like:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf10 \cb9 Fetch all sources in parallel to save time. Then extract and write\
one source at a time \'97 extract from source 1, write to working file,\
confirm, then extract from source 2, write, confirm, and so on.\
Do not batch the extractions or writes.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 This would likely cut the Phase 2 time roughly in half since the fetches are the slowest part \'97 each Jina call takes 5\'9615 seconds and right now they run sequentially. With parallel fetching you'd get all the raw article text in one batch, then process them one by one for extraction.\
Worth adding to v4 of the prompt. For now let the current run finish \'97 changing it mid-run isn't possible, and the one-at-a-time approach will still complete, just more slowly.\
