\cf2 It's a real constraint and worth thinking through carefully. Here are the options available to us within what Claude Code can actually do:\
\
Option 1 \'97 More searches, more angles\
The most reliable mitigation is simply running more searches with more varied queries. Instead of 12 searches we ask for 20-25, and we prescribe specific angles that are less likely to surface the same top-10 results repeatedly:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls84\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Neighbourhood-level queries ("best restaurants Gr\'e0cia Barcelona 2025") surface different results than city-wide queries\
\ls84\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Forum and community queries ("Barcelona restaurants Reddit 2025", "foro gastronomia Barcelona 2025") tend to surface grassroots recommendations\
\ls84\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Writer-first queries ("food journalist Barcelona 2025 blog") surface individual writers rather than publications\
\ls84\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Social media adjacent queries ("Barcelona food writer Instagram 2025") sometimes surface bloggers who rank poorly on Google but have strong local followings\
\ls84\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Query in Catalan ("on menjar Barcelona 2025 recomanacions locals") surfaces completely different results than the same query in Spanish or English\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Each of these angles hits a different segment of the search index and returns a different set of 10 results. Twenty targeted queries covering different angles effectively gives you 200 distinct results to evaluate, with much less overlap than 20 generic queries would produce.\
\
Option 2 \'97 Explicit diversity instruction\
Add an instruction that forces Claude Code to ensure source diversity before proceeding. Something like:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf10 \cb9 Before finalising your source list, verify:\
- At least 2 sources must be in Catalan (CA)\
- At least 2 sources must be primary local voices (blogger or local press)\
- No more than 2 sources from global brands (Time Out, Infatuation etc)\
- At least 1 source must be from a publication not previously used in\
  any LocalBite city pack\
If these conditions are not met, run additional searches until they are\
or explain why they cannot be met for this city.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 This forces the pipeline to keep searching until it finds local voices rather than stopping when it has enough high-ranking global sources.\
\
Option 3 \'97 Follow-on searches from snippets\
Search result snippets often contain clues about other sources \'97 mentions of other publications, writer names, or related articles. We could add an instruction to extract any publication names or writer names mentioned in search snippets and run follow-on searches specifically for those:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf10 \cb9 After each search, scan the result snippets for mentions of other food\
writers, bloggers, or publications not yet in your candidate list. Run\
a follow-on search for any promising names found this way.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 This creates a chain of discovery where one search leads to the next, similar to how a human researcher would follow cross-references.\
\
Option 4 \'97 Structured search plan before execution\
Instead of running searches and evaluating results as it goes, ask Claude Code to first design a search plan covering all the angles, then execute it. This prevents it from stopping early when it has found enough obvious sources:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf10 \cb9 Before running any searches, write a search plan to\
localbite-barcelona-search-plan.txt listing at least 20 queries across\
these dimensions: city-wide EN, city-wide ES, city-wide CA, per-neighbourhood\
EN, per-neighbourhood ES, writer-first, forum/community, food award\
coverage, recent opening coverage, and social media adjacent. Then execute\
the plan in full before evaluating any sources.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \
Option 5 \'97 Web fetch of aggregator pages\
Some pages aggregate local food writers and bloggers \'97 "best food blogs in Barcelona", "mejores blogs gastronomicos de Barcelona". Fetching one of these pages via Jina gives us a curated list of local voices that we'd never find by searching for restaurants directly. We could add a dedicated step:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf10 \cb9 Before Phase 1 source searches, run 3 searches specifically for\
aggregator pages that list Barcelona food bloggers and writers. Fetch\
the top result from each search via Jina and extract any blogger or\
writer names mentioned. Add these to your candidate pool before running\
the main source discovery searches.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 \
My recommendation for v4\
Combine Options 1, 2, and 5 \'97 they complement each other well and none of them add significant complexity or time to the pipeline:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls85\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Prescribe 20-25 searches with specific angle categories (Option 1)\
\ls85\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Add the diversity verification gate before source finalisation (Option 2)\
\ls85\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Add a pre-Phase-1 aggregator fetch step to seed the candidate pool with local bloggers (Option 5)\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Option 3 (follow-on searches from snippets) is also good but harder to control reliably in a prompt. Option 4 (search plan file) adds useful transparency but the benefit may not justify the extra step given the other improvements.\
Together these three changes would meaningfully improve the chances of finding genuine local voices rather than always defaulting to the same high-ranking global publications. They would also make the search log more interesting to read \'97 you'd see a deliberate progression through different angles rather than a handful of similar queries.\
Shall I incorporate these into the v4 prompt when the Barcelona run finishes?\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
