\fs32 \cf2 Heavy pipeline use across multiple cities in a week could still hit weekly caps even on Max 20x.\
My honest recommendation\
Max 5x at $100/month is worth considering if you plan to run the pipeline regularly \'97 say two or three cities per week. It would likely cut the interruption-related delays significantly and reduce crashes. But it won't cut the run time in half on its own.\
The combination of Max 5x plus the v4 prompt improvements (parallel fetches, paired extraction batching, moving export out of Claude Code) would together bring a 37-minute run down to probably 12-15 minutes with no interruptions.\
If you're only running one city every week or two, the Pro plan with the v4 optimisations is probably sufficient and saves $80/month.\
