\fs32 \cf2 Assessed comprehensive output for iterative refinement\
\
Excellent run \'97 and only 4m 46s for the export step compared to the 37 minutes total. The export utility script would have made that instant, but the intermediate saves clearly helped. Let me give you a thorough assessment before we build v4.\
\
What v3 got right\
The source diversity is dramatically better than any previous run. Three genuine Catalan-language primary sources appeared for the first time \'97 Ara.cat (Rosa Rod\'f3n), ElNacional.cat (Oriol Foix), and a new entrant, Fancy Nancista (Nancy). Both-pool detection correctly identified 6 entries with genuine cross-language confirmation rather than sibling edition inflation.\
The writer names are now credited properly \'97 Isabelle Kliger at The Infatuation, Lourdes L\'f3pez at Gu\'eda Repsol, Anna Torrents at The New Barcelona Post, Ricard Mart\'edn at Time Out. This is a meaningful improvement for the product's editorial credibility.\
The two-detail rule for secondary sources worked \'97 Time Out contributed only 3 single-source entries (Bar Puntal, Casa Luz, La Sosenga) versus the 40 it dominated with in previous runs. That's the concentration problem solved without needing the cap to fire.\
The raw and final file split worked perfectly \'97 localbite-barcelona-raw.json preserves the pre-review state and localbite-barcelona-2025-2026.json is the clean final pack.\
The search log was written in real time this time \'97 22 queries logged, no reconstruction note. The search transparency is now genuinely useful.\
\
What needs fixing in v4\
The search log has repeated queries \'97 the same query appears 3-4 times in the log because Claude Code ran it multiple times to confirm different sources. The v4 search plan written to file before execution should prevent this redundancy.\
Beteve.cat yielded 0 restaurants \'97 it was fetched but the article was a news bulletin with no per-restaurant descriptions. The pipeline correctly handled this but it wasted a fetch slot. The pre-fetch URL preview step in v4 should catch this before committing to a full fetch.\
6 both-pool entries is lower than ideal \'97 with 9 sources across EN, ES, and CA we'd expect more cross-confirmation. This suggests the CA sources (Ara, ElNacional, Beteve) are covering different restaurants than the EN sources rather than independently confirming the same ones. This is actually editorially interesting \'97 it means the Catalan press is recommending genuinely different places than the English press. Worth surfacing in the pack rather than treating as a problem.\
Some Tier B entries have thin quotes \'97 entries like Bar Siberia ("Small traditional bar in Poblenou serving classic Catalan dishes for under \'8020") and Bar Iberia ("Traditional bar run by brothers... serving classic Catalan cuisine at reasonable prices") passed Tier B but are borderline. The v4 quote quality check should be stricter.\
The source_type on some entries looks wrong \'97 Bar Super is tagged "secondary" even though it's confirmed by both The Infatuation and Time Out, neither of which is wrong but both being secondary means the source_type should flag this. Worth adding a note in v4 that "secondary + secondary" multi-source entries should still be clearly distinguished from "primary + primary" ones.\
\
New v4 additions from this run\
