STEP 1 \'97 Write search plan\
Before running any searches, write a search plan to\
[OUTPUT_SEARCH_PLAN] covering exactly 20 queries across these angles:\
\
Angle A \'97 City-wide EN (3 queries)\
Angle B \'97 City-wide [LANGUAGE_PRIMARY] (3 queries)\
Angle C \'97 Per-neighbourhood EN (3 queries, different neighbourhoods\
  from GEOGRAPHIC_BOUNDARY_INCLUDE)\
Angle D \'97 Per-neighbourhood [LANGUAGE_PRIMARY] (3 queries)\
Angle E \'97 Writer-first (2 queries: "food journalist [CITY] 2025",\
  "[LANGUAGE_PRIMARY] food critic [CITY] blog 2026")\
Angle F \'97 Forum and community (2 queries: "[CITY] restaurants Reddit\
  2025 recommendations", "forum gastronomia [CITY] 2025")\
Angle G \'97 Recent openings (2 queries: "new restaurants [CITY] 2025\
  opening", "nuevos restaurantes [CITY] 2026 apertura")\
Angle H \'97 Awards and recognition (2 queries: "best new restaurant\
  [CITY] 2025 award critic", "Michelin [CITY] 2026 recomendados\
  bib gourmand")\
\
Each query must be meaningfully distinct. Write all 20 to the plan\
file before running any of them.\
\
STEP 2 \'97 Execute search plan\
Run all 20 searches. After each search append to [OUTPUT_SEARCH_LOG].\
Do not stop early \'97 run the full plan even if you have found enough\
candidates after 10 searches.\
\
STEP 3 \'97 Evaluate candidates\
From all search results, identify candidate sources. For each\
candidate, perform a quick verification fetch via Jina to confirm:\
- Article publication date is 2025 or 2026 (check article text,\
  not page metadata or "updated" date)\
- Article has a named author\
- Article is specifically about [CITY] restaurants (not all of\
  [COUNTRY] or a wider region)\
- Page returns substantive content (over 2,000 chars) confirming\
  it is a genuine article, not a category page or directory\
\
If verification fetch returns under 2,000 chars or no publication\
date is visible, reject the source without counting it as a fetch.\
\
SOURCE QUALITY RULES:\

\f2 \uc0\u10003 
\f0  Accept: named author, 2025\'962026 publication date, specific\
  restaurant guide, editorial independence\

\f2 \uc0\u10003 
\f0  Accept: local blogger with evidence of [CITY] residency or\
  regular coverage\

\f6 \uc0\u10007 
\f0  Reject: no named author\

\f6 \uc0\u10007 
\f0  Reject: pre-2025 publication date (check fetched text, not\
  "updated" label)\

\f6 \uc0\u10007 
\f0  Reject: booking sites, hotel sites, sponsored content\

\f6 \uc0\u10007 
\f0  Reject: covers all of [COUNTRY] rather than [CITY] specifically\

\f6 \uc0\u10007 
\f0  Reject: any URL in KNOWN_PROBLEMATIC_URLS\
\
SOURCE WEIGHTING:\

\f1 \uc0\u9888 
\f0  Secondary sources (from SECONDARY_SOURCES list): acceptable but\
  not primary local voices. Apply stricter evidence rules to their\
  single-source entries in Phase 3. Maximum 30 restaurants extracted\
  from any secondary source article.\

\f2 \uc0\u10003 
\f0  Primary sources: named local bloggers, local newspaper food\
  sections, independent food writers based in [CITY], expat writers\
  with documented long-term residence. Standard evidence rules apply.\
\
SIBLING EDITION CHECK:\
If a publication has editions in multiple languages (e.g. Time Out\
in EN and [LANGUAGE_PRIMARY]), verify they are independently produced\
before treating as separate language pools. If same editorial team\
or same restaurant list, count as one source only.\
\
DIVERSITY GATE \'97 do not proceed to Phase 2 until met:\

\f2 \uc0\u10003 
\f0  At least 2 EN primary sources\

\f2 \uc0\u10003 
\f0  At least 2 [LANGUAGE_PRIMARY] primary sources\

\f2 \uc0\u10003 
\f0  At least 1 source not previously used in any LocalBite city pack\

\f2 \uc0\u10003 
\f0  No more than 2 secondary sources in total\
\
If diversity gate not met after 20 searches, run up to 5 additional\
targeted searches for the missing category, then proceed with what\
you have and report which criteria were not met.\
\
Select 8\'9612 sources that pass all criteria. For each state:\
publication, writer, URL, language, article date, source type\
(primary/secondary), and one sentence on why it passes.\
\
Do not stop for approval. Proceed to Phase 2.\
