For each source follow this exact sequence:\
1. Fetch via https://r.jina.ai/ prepended to URL\
2. Report fetch quality\
3. Extract restaurants from that source only\
4. Write extracted restaurants to [OUTPUT_WORKING] (append)\
5. Confirm write succeeded\
6. Move to next source\
\
Fetch all sources in parallel (send all Jina requests simultaneously)\
then process extractions one source at a time in the order they\
return. This saves time without risking token limit errors.\
\
For each source report:\
- Publication and writer\
- Characters returned (truncated if over 500,000)\
- Fetch quality: good (over 3,000), partial (1,000\'963,000),\
  failed (under 1,000)\
- Source type: primary / secondary\
- Restaurants extracted (count)\
- Confirmed written to working file: yes / no\
\
If failed: skip, note reason, continue.\
If partial: extract with caution, mark entries low-confidence.\
\
EXTRACTION RULES:\

\f2 \uc0\u10003 
\f0  Only include restaurants explicitly named in fetched article text\

\f2 \uc0\u10003 
\f0  Extract per restaurant: name, neighbourhood, price level,\
  signature dish (if mentioned), quote (writer's words paraphrased),\
  cuisine type (from article text), opening year (if mentioned)\

\f6 \uc0\u10007 
\f0  Do not use training knowledge to add restaurants not in the text\

\f6 \uc0\u10007 
\f0  Do not include if only evidence is a list title or section header\

\f6 \uc0\u10007 
\f0  Secondary sources: maximum 30 restaurants extracted\
\
QUOTE QUALITY RULE:\
A valid quote must be at least 15 words and contain at least one\
specific detail: dish name, chef name, physical description, price,\
year, or neighbourhood. Quotes under 15 words or with no specific\
detail 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  mark entry as low-confidence.\
\
For secondary source entries: quote must contain at least TWO\
specific details. If only one: mark as low-confidence (will become\
