\fs32 \cf2 Assessed rate limit impact and identified viable workaround solution\
\
Frustrating timing \'97 but the good news is that Claude Code wrote the raw JSON file before hitting the limit. This is exactly why we built the export utility script.\
Open a new Terminal window and run:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf10 \cb9 cd ~/localbite\
node localbite-export.js localbite-barcelona-raw.json localbite-barcelona-2025-2026.json 10 28 34 37 43 46\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 Press Enter. The script will apply all six removals and write the final clean JSON in under a second \'97 no Claude Code needed.\
The limit resets at 8am Toronto time, so you can come back then if you want Claude Code to write the research summary and update the journal for this run. Or paste the output here and I can draft those files for you now using the export script's output.\
