\cf2 Good question to revisit given what we now know about how the pipeline actually runs.\
\
The current situation on Claude Pro\
Claude Pro gives you roughly 45 prompts per 5-hour rolling window. The problem is that Claude Code's pipeline isn't 1 prompt \'97 each search, each fetch, each extraction, each file write counts as activity against your limit. The Barcelona v4 run probably consumed the equivalent of 20-30 prompts worth of limit in 26 minutes, which is why you hit the ceiling before the export step.\
\
The options\
Claude Pro ($20/month \'97 what you have) What you're experiencing now. Good enough for one city run at a time with gaps between. The rate limit resets on a rolling 5-hour window so you can run again after waiting. The export utility script helps because it moves the final step outside Claude Code entirely.\
Claude Max 5x ($100/month) Five times the usage of Pro. In practice this means you could likely run 2-3 full city pipelines back to back without hitting a limit. The Barcelona run that crashed at the export step almost certainly wouldn't have crashed on Max 5x. The $80/month difference pays for itself if rate limit interruptions are costing you more than one session per week.\
Claude Max 20x ($200/month) Twenty times Pro. Effectively removes rate limits as a practical concern for this use case. Designed for heavy daily use. Probably more than you need for running one city at a time.\
API pay-as-you-go This is what the original 
