\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  terminal script was designed for. You pay per token rather than a flat subscription. For a single city run the cost would be roughly $0.10-0.30 at current Sonnet 4.6 prices. No rate limits in the same sense \'97 just per-minute throughput limits that scale with your API tier. The downside is you need to manage the API key and billing separately, and the terminal script doesn't have all the v4 improvements baked in yet.\
\
My honest recommendation for your current usage pattern\
You're running roughly one city every few days in focused sessions. Claude Pro is workable with the export script as a safety net. The main friction is the occasional rate limit crash mid-session, which the export script now handles for the final step.\
If you find yourself wanting to run multiple cities in a single sitting \'97 say, Valencia, Barcelona, and Lisbon in one afternoon \'97 Max 5x would be worth it. At your current pace, Pro is probably sufficient.\
