\cf2 Clean run \'97 21 minutes total, no crashes, export completed in under 3 minutes. The export step is clearly much faster now that it's separated from the main pipeline.\
Assessment of the Fes pack\
10 restaurants from 3 sources is thin but honest. The pipeline did exactly what it should \'97 it searched hard (29 searches, 9 additional Arabic searches), reported clearly what it couldn't find, and produced a small but verified pack rather than padding it with weak sources.\
The three sources are interesting:\
Anita's Feast \'97 a food-focused travel writer, EN primary. This is the kind of source the pipeline is designed to find \'97 independent, named, specific to Fes.\
MarocLovers / Myriam \'97 a French-language local source. This is the genuinely valuable one. A French-speaking local writing about Fes restaurants for a Moroccan audience is closer to ground truth than any English travel writer.\
Sainsbury's Magazine / Leah Hyslop \'97 a UK food magazine. Worth noting this is borderline \'97 a UK supermarket magazine is closer to secondary than primary. But if it passed the quality criteria with a named author and specific 2025-2026 content, it's valid.\
The Arabic gap is the most significant finding\
Nine additional targeted searches found no named-author Arabic-language Fes restaurant articles from 2025-2026. This could mean several things \'97 Moroccan Arabic food writing exists but isn't indexed well by search engines, or it's behind paywalls, or Hespress and Goud.ma simply don't publish the kind of specific restaurant guides our pipeline looks for. Worth noting for v5 \'97 a direct fetch of those publications' food sections rather than relying on search discovery might work better for Arabic sources.\
How to think about this pack\
The Fes pack is most valuable as a proof of concept and a stress test rather than a production-ready city guide. 10 restaurants is too few to be genuinely useful to a traveller. But the methodology worked \'97 it found real sources, extracted real recommendations, and was honest about its limitations.\
For a genuinely useful Fes pack you'd probably need to supplement the pipeline with manual research \'97 reaching out to Myriam at MarocLovers directly, looking at Moroccan travel forums, or finding a local food writer contact. That's the human-in-the-loop element that the pipeline can't replace for underserved cities.\
