STEP 1 \'97 Write search plan\
Before running any searches, write a plan to\
./localbite-marrakesh-search-plan.txt covering exactly 22 queries\
across these angles:\
\
Angle A \'97 City-wide EN (3 queries)\
Angle B \'97 City-wide FR (3 queries)\
Angle C \'97 City-wide AR (3 queries \'97 more than Fes given larger\
  Arabic food writing scene in Marrakesh)\
Angle D \'97 Per-neighbourhood EN (2 queries \'97 medina and Gueliz)\
Angle E \'97 Per-neighbourhood FR (2 queries)\
Angle F \'97 Per-neighbourhood AR (1 query)\
Angle G \'97 Writer-first (2 queries)\
Angle H \'97 Forum and community (2 queries)\
Angle I \'97 Recent openings (2 queries)\
Angle J \'97 Awards and recognition (2 queries)\
\
Each query must be meaningfully distinct. Write all 22 before\
running any of them.\
\
STEP 2 \'97 Execute search plan\
Run all 22 searches. Log each after it runs. Do not stop early.\
\
STEP 3 \'97 Evaluate candidates\
For each candidate, run a quick verification fetch via Jina to\
confirm:\
- Publication date is 2025 or 2026 (check article text not metadata)\
- Named author present\
- Article is specifically about Marrakesh restaurants\
- Page returns over 2,000 chars\
\
If under 2,000 chars or no date visible, reject without using a\
full fetch slot.\
\
SOURCE QUALITY RULES:\

\f2 \uc0\u10003 
\f0  Accept: named author, 2025\'962026 date, specific restaurant guide,\
  editorial independence\

\f2 \uc0\u10003 
\f0  Accept: local blogger with evidence of Marrakesh residency or\
  regular coverage\

\f2 \uc0\u10003 
\f0  Accept: Moroccan food writer based elsewhere who has written a\
  specific Marrakesh restaurant guide in 2025 or 2026\

\f6 \uc0\u10007 
\f0  Reject: no named author\

\f6 \uc0\u10007 
\f0  Reject: pre-2025 date (verify from fetched text not "updated"\
  label)\

\f6 \uc0\u10007 
\f0  Reject: booking sites, hotel sites, sponsored content\

\f6 \uc0\u10007 
\f0  Reject: covers all of Morocco not Marrakesh specifically\

\f6 \uc0\u10007 
\f0  Reject: gastronomistas.com\
\
SOURCE WEIGHTING:\

\f1 \uc0\u9888 
\f0  Secondary (Cond\'e9 Nast, Lonely Planet, Time Out): acceptable but\
  not primary local voices. Stricter evidence rules. Max 30\
  restaurants extracted.\

\f2 \uc0\u10003 
\f0  Primary: named local bloggers, Moroccan press, independent writers\
  based in Marrakesh or with documented regular coverage.\
\
WRITER PROFILE \'97 NEW in v5:\
For every source that passes quality criteria, write a 2-3 sentence\
writer profile covering:\
- Who the writer is and their background\
- Their connection to Marrakesh or Morocco (resident, regular\
  visitor, local press)\
- Their editorial stance (independent, no advertising, pays for\
  meals, or note if unclear)\
\
Store this in the sources array as writer_profile field. This will\
be used in the viewer to help English-speaking readers understand\
why a French or Arabic source is credible.\
\
SIBLING EDITION CHECK:\
If a publication has FR and AR editions, verify they are\
independently produced before treating as separate language pools.\
\
DIVERSITY GATE:\

\f2 \uc0\u10003 
\f0  At least 1 EN primary source\

\f2 \uc0\u10003 
\f0  At least 1 FR or AR primary source\

\f2 \uc0\u10003 
\f0  No more than 2 secondary sources in total\
\
If gate not met after 22 searches run up to 8 additional targeted\
searches. Report which criteria were not met.\
\
Select 6\'9612 sources. For each state: publication, writer, URL,\
language, article date, source type, writer profile, one sentence\
on why it passes.\
\
Do not stop for approval. Proceed to Phase 2.\
