\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Anthropic doesn't publicly disclose which search provider powers the web search tool. Based on what's publicly known it's likely a combination of providers rather than a single one, but Anthropic hasn't confirmed the specifics.\
What we do know:\
It's not a direct Google Search API \'97 Google's search API is called Programmable Search Engine and has significant limitations on what it returns. The results Claude Code gets look more comprehensive than what that API typically produces.\
Brave Search is a known Anthropic partner \'97 Anthropic has a documented relationship with Brave Search for some of its search capabilities. Brave operates an independent search index rather than licensing Google's results, which is why searches sometimes surface different results than you'd get on google.com.\
The results behave differently from Google \'97 if you compare the same query run in Claude Code versus typed into Google, you'll often see different results. This is consistent with a non-Google provider.\
Why it matters for LocalBite \'97 if the search index is Brave rather than Google, it may explain some of the source discovery patterns we've seen. Brave's index is generally good for mainstream content but may index Arabic-language content differently than Google does, which could contribute to the Arabic gap we found in the Fes run.\
If knowing the exact provider matters for the project, the most reliable way to find out would be to check Anthropic's current documentation at docs.anthropic.com \'97 they may have disclosed more details since my knowledge cutoff.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
