\cf2 Quick answer \'97 you can't use GitHub Pages with a private repository on the free plan. GitHub Pages only works with public repositories on free accounts.\
You have two options:\
\
Option 1 \'97 Keep it public but obscure\
Leave the repository public but don't share the URL widely. A public GitHub repository that nobody knows about is effectively private in practice \'97 it won't appear in search results unless someone knows your username. This is what most early-stage projects do.\
The viewer URL 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 https://localbiteadmin.github.io/localbite/
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  won't be discoverable unless you share it or someone specifically searches for your GitHub username.\
\
Option 2 \'97 Upgrade to GitHub Pro\
GitHub Pro costs $4/month and allows private repositories with GitHub Pages. This means:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls168\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The repository code is hidden from the public\
\ls168\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
But the GitHub Pages URL still works for anyone you share it with\
\ls168\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
You control who can see the source code\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 This is the right option if you want to keep the underlying JSON data and pipeline prompts private while still sharing the viewer URL selectively.\
\
My honest recommendation\
For now stay on the free plan with the public repository. The data is already public \'97 it's all sourced from publicly available articles. The pipeline prompts and JSON files don't contain anything sensitive. The obscurity of an unknown URL is sufficient protection for an early-stage project.\
When you're ready to share more widely or want to protect the codebase, upgrading to GitHub Pro at $4/month is a small cost for meaningful privacy control.\
Which feels right for where you are now?\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
