\fs32 \cf2 Evaluated free mapping solutions for restaurant coordinate collection\
\
Good news \'97 for 24 restaurants total (10 Fes + 14 Marrakesh) this is very achievable for free. Here's the full picture:\
\
The free tool: Nominatim\
Nominatim is OpenStreetMap's geocoding service. You give it a place name and city and it returns latitude/longitude coordinates. It's completely free, no API key required, no account needed, no rate limit for light use.\
The URL format is simply:\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf10 \cb9 https://nominatim.openstreetmap.org/search?q=Nomad+Marrakesh&format=json\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 For well-known restaurants in tourist cities like Marrakesh and Fes, Nominatim often has the exact location because OpenStreetMap contributors have mapped them. For smaller or newer places it may return the neighbourhood or street level \'97 still much better than a centroid.\
\
What it would take\
A Claude Code script that:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls195\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Reads 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 localbite-fes-2025-2026.json
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  and 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 localbite-marrakesh-2025-2026.json
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 \
\ls195\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
For each restaurant, sends a Nominatim query with restaurant name + city\
\ls195\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Records the returned coordinates and a confidence level\
\ls195\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Writes the coordinates back into the JSON as 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 lat
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  and 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 lng
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  fields\
\ls195\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	5	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Flags any that returned low-confidence results for manual verification\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 For 24 restaurants this would run in about 2-3 minutes. Nominatim asks for a 1-second delay between requests for polite use, so 24 requests = roughly 30 seconds of actual API time.\
\
Realistic accuracy expectations\
For Marrakesh specifically, several of the restaurants are well-known enough that Nominatim will find them precisely \'97 Nomad, Dar Yacout, La Grande Table Marocaine, and Dardar Rooftop are all likely in OpenStreetMap. The smaller French-sourced entries like Palais Soleiman and SABO may be harder to find.\
For Fes, Caf\'e9 Clock is definitely in OpenStreetMap. The MarocLovers-sourced restaurants are less certain.\
Rough estimate: probably 15-18 of the 24 will geocode precisely, 6-9 will need manual verification.\
\
Manual verification for the rest\
For any that don't geocode cleanly, the fallback is simple \'97 open OpenStreetMap in a browser, search for the restaurant, right-click the location and copy the coordinates. Takes about 30 seconds per restaurant. For 6-9 restaurants that's under 5 minutes of manual work.\
\
What to do with the coordinates once you have them\
Add 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 lat
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  and 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 lng
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  fields to each restaurant object in the JSON. The viewer map code can then use exact coordinates instead of neighbourhood centroids for those two cities, while still falling back to centroids for Barcelona and Valencia until those are enriched too.\
\
