\cf2 No \'97 I was talking about Nominatim's accuracy, not comparing it to the index file. Let me clarify what I meant.\
The index file (
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 localbite-index.json
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 ) is a separate thing entirely \'97 it's the city directory that tells the viewer which city packs exist and where to find them. It has nothing to do with coordinates.\
What I was saying about Nominatim is simply that its geocoding accuracy varies by restaurant:\
High confidence \'97 well-known restaurants that OpenStreetMap contributors have already mapped with a precise pin. Nominatim returns exact coordinates. For Marrakesh this likely covers Nomad, Dar Yacout, La Grande Table Marocaine, Dardar Rooftop.\
Lower confidence \'97 smaller, newer, or less prominent restaurants that aren't in OpenStreetMap yet, or where the name is ambiguous. Nominatim might return the street, the neighbourhood, or nothing at all. For these the Claude Code script would flag them and you'd verify manually on openstreetmap.org.\
So the script doesn't replace or interact with the index file at all \'97 it just reads the two Moroccan city pack JSONs, queries Nominatim for each restaurant name, and writes coordinates back into those same JSON files.\
