\fs28 \cf6 Weighed free mapping alternatives against Google's superior automated accuracy\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 Weighed free mapping alternatives against Google's superior automated accuracy\
\
Honest answer \'97 not really, for fully automated accuracy matching Google Maps Place IDs at scale.\
Here's why, and what the realistic free options actually are:\
\
Why Google Maps Place IDs are hard to match for free\
Google's database has three things working in its favour that free alternatives lack:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls197\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Business verification \'97 restaurant owners claim their listings and confirm their own address\
\ls197\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Coverage depth \'97 even small local restaurants in Fes and Marrakesh are likely in Google Maps because tourists use it to navigate there\
\ls197\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Stable unique identifiers \'97 a Place ID never changes even if the restaurant moves or changes name\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 No free service has all three of these.\
\
The realistic free alternatives\
Nominatim / OpenStreetMap \'97 best free option overall. Accuracy is excellent for well-known tourist-facing restaurants, patchy for smaller local places. For Marrakesh and Fes specifically, coverage is probably 60-75% precise, the rest needs manual verification. Fully automated but not fully accurate.\
Foursquare Places API \'97 has a free tier (limited to a certain number of requests per day). Better coverage than Nominatim for restaurants specifically because Foursquare was built as a venue database. Accuracy is close to Google Maps for popular venues. The free tier is enough for 24 restaurants. Worth trying.\
OpenStreetMap Overpass API \'97 queries the raw OSM database directly rather than through Nominatim. More flexible than Nominatim for finding venues by name and category within a bounding box. Same underlying data but sometimes surfaces results Nominatim misses.\
Wikidata \'97 a small number of well-known restaurants have Wikidata entries with coordinates. Only covers the most prominent venues. Not useful for our scale.\
\
