\fs32 \cf2 Synthesized Google Maps API pricing for geocoding use case\
\
Here's the honest picture for your specific use case:\
\
For the geocoding task specifically (finding coordinates for restaurants)\
Google now offers
\fs24 \cf4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://nicolalazzari.ai/articles/understanding-google-maps-apis-a-comprehensive-guide-to-uses-and-costs"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb27 Nicola Lazzari\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf28 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 free monthly usage caps per SKU. Geocoding is an Essentials SKU which gets 10,000 free monthly events.\
For 138 restaurants across four cities, you'd use 138 geocoding requests total \'97 well within the 10,000 free monthly cap. So the geocoding pass itself would cost nothing under Google's current pricing.\
\
For displaying the map in the viewer\
This is where costs could appear. Dynamic Maps (interactive maps with zoom and pan) cost $7 per 1,000 requests after the free cap.
\fs24 \cf4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://nicolalazzari.ai/articles/understanding-google-maps-apis-a-comprehensive-guide-to-uses-and-costs"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb27 Nicola Lazzari\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf28 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 But your viewer uses Leaflet with OpenStreetMap tiles \'97 not Google Maps \'97 so map display costs nothing regardless.\
If you ever switched to Google Maps tiles for display, you'd pay per map load once you exceed the free tier.\
\
Bottom line for LocalBite at current scale\
For what you're doing right now \'97 geocoding 138 restaurants once and displaying them on an OpenStreetMap/Leaflet map \'97 the Google Places API would cost nothing. You'd stay well within the free tier.\
The cost concern only becomes relevant at scale \'97 if the viewer gets thousands of users making Places API calls per session, or if you start using Google Maps tiles instead of OpenStreetMap. Neither of those applies at v1.\
\
So why proceed with Nominatim + Foursquare?\
Two reasons that still hold even knowing the free tier covers your current scale:\
First, Google requires a billing account with a credit card on file even for free usage. If something goes wrong or usage spikes unexpectedly, charges appear automatically.\
Second, Google's terms of service restrict using Place IDs and coordinates outside of Google Maps \'97 meaning you technically can't geocode with Google and then display on an OpenStreetMap/Leaflet map. You'd need to display on Google Maps if you use their data.\
Nominatim has no such restriction. The coordinates are yours to use anywhere.\
So the free approach we're already building is genuinely the right one for LocalBite \'97 not just cheaper but also terms-of-service compliant. Shall we proceed with running the geocoding script?\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
