\cf2 The caveat banner in the viewer automatically adjusts to tell users how many pins are verified vs approximate. So a user sees something like "11 pins show verified locations \'b7 5 show approximate neighbourhood centres" \'97 honest and clear.\
The only downside is that for restaurants with null coordinates, users can't navigate directly to them from the map. They'd need to use the source link on the card to find the exact address. That's acceptable for a v1 product especially with a clear caveat shown.\
