\fs32 \cf2 Nominatim finds roughly 30-60% of restaurants correctly but produces false positives in every city. The false positives are particularly dangerous \'97 they look like successes but are silently wrong. Without manual verification we'd have restaurants pinned in Ghana, Toronto, and random Moroccan locations.\
\
Foursquare performance for Rabat\
Foursquare was supposed to help with the restaurants Nominatim missed \'97 but looking at the Rabat results, Foursquare also returned zero additional finds. All 5 manual entries were found via Google Maps, not Foursquare. So for this run Foursquare contributed nothing.\
\
Key lessons\
1. False positives are the biggest risk Nominatim matches on restaurant name globally, not within a city boundary. Common restaurant names (Marea, +61, Benyamna) match locations in completely wrong countries. Every Nominatim result needs a coordinate sanity check \'97 is it within the expected lat/lng range for this city?\
2. Foursquare didn't add value for Moroccan cities The free tier may not have good coverage for smaller Moroccan restaurants. It worked for zero of the Rabat misses. This could be because the restaurants are too local, too new, or Foursquare's Morocco coverage is thin.\
3. Google Maps manual lookup is the most reliable method Every manually verified coordinate was found quickly on Google Maps. For 10-15 restaurants per city it takes 15-20 minutes and produces accurate results.\
4. The geocoding script needs a bounding box check The script should automatically reject any result outside the expected coordinate range for the target city. For Morocco this would be latitude 27-36, longitude -2 to -14. This would have caught Marea (Ghana) and +61 (Toronto) automatically without needing manual review.\
\
What this means for Chefchaouen\
Chefchaouen will likely have fewer restaurants than Rabat or Marrakesh \'97 probably 8-12 given the thin source pool expected. Nominatim will find maybe 3-5, Foursquare will likely add nothing, and Google Maps manual lookup will be needed for the rest.\
Given this pattern the most efficient approach for Chefchaouen is:\
