\fs32 \cf2 For the LocalBite pipeline \'97 which follows structured rules rather than open-ended reasoning \'97 standard Sonnet 4.6 would likely perform just as well while consuming 2-3x less of your rate limit quota.\
The pipeline rules (concentration cap, diversity gate, tier assignment) do the heavy reasoning work. Extended thinking mainly helps when rules conflict or edge cases arise \'97 which is rare in a well-defined pipeline.\
My updated recommendation:\
Switch to standard Sonnet 4.6 for LocalBite pipeline runs. You'd likely run 2-3x more cities per session before hitting the rate limit. Keep extended thinking for complex open-ended tasks in this chat.\
