Why Foursquare failed for Morocco\
In Morocco, Foursquare added zero value across three cities. But the reasons are specific to Morocco:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls284\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Moroccan restaurants are primarily discovered via Google Maps by tourists\
\ls284\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Foursquare's venue database has historically weak coverage in North Africa\
\ls284\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Many Moroccan restaurants don't have consistent Latin-script names making matching harder\
\ls284\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The restaurants we were looking for were often small family-run places in medinas not the kind of venues Foursquare indexes well\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
Why Foursquare might perform better for well-documented countries\
Foursquare's strength is cities where:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls285\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Restaurant owners actively manage their digital presence\
\ls285\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The food scene is covered by tech-savvy food writers who use Foursquare\
\ls285\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Venue names are consistent across platforms\
\ls285\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The city has a strong "going out" culture with active check-in behaviour\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 This describes Copenhagen, Lisbon, Porto, Edinburgh, and most Western European cities well. Foursquare's European coverage is significantly stronger than its North African coverage.\
\
The honest unknown\
We only tested Foursquare on Moroccan cities where it was always going to struggle. We have no data on how it performs for European cities. The fair answer is we don't actually know yet.\
\
What the data would look like if Foursquare worked well\
For a well-documented European city with say 50 restaurants:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls286\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Nominatim v3 with bounding box: probably 60-70% hit rate (based on Chefchaouen's 65%)\
\ls286\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Foursquare on the remaining 15-20 misses: unknown, but potentially 50-70% of those\
\ls286\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Manual Google Maps: only needed for the remaining 5-10\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 That would reduce manual geocoding from ~15-20 lookups per city to ~5-10 \'97 meaningful time saving across 10 cities.\
\
What I'd suggest\
Test Foursquare on the first automated city \'97 Lisbon is the natural choice since the prompt is already prepared. Run the geocoding script with your Foursquare API key and compare:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls287\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
How many Nominatim finds\
\ls287\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
How many Foursquare adds on top\
\ls287\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
How many still need manual lookup\
\ls287\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Any false positives from Foursquare\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 That gives us real data for a well-documented European city before committing to using Foursquare across a 10-city batch.\
The bounding box validation in v3 already applies to Foursquare results too \'97 so false positives are caught regardless.\
\
Bottom line\
Yes, Foursquare is worth including for well-documented European countries \'97 but we should verify it actually helps on Lisbon before relying on it for a 10-city batch. One test run will tell us more than any amount of theorising based on Moroccan results.\
