\fs32 \cf2 What this means practically\
For the viewer today \'97 mostly handled gracefully. The viewer checks whether fields exist before displaying them. Writer profiles only appear in the Sources panel for v5 cities. The cuisine filter auto-hides when no cuisine data exists (Valencia). MAD vs \'80 pricing is handled correctly.\
For the map \'97 Barcelona and Valencia have no coordinates at all. They fall back entirely to neighbourhood centroids. This is the biggest functional gap \'97 the map is genuinely useful for Morocco cities but decorative for Spain cities.\
For future automation \'97 if you build an orchestrator that processes all cities the same way, missing fields will either cause errors or silently produce incomplete output. Code needs to handle nullable fields throughout.\
For data integrity \'97 the 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 both_pool_count
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  field in localbite-index.json may not be accurate for Valencia since the v3 schema handled language pools differently.\
\
The three options\
Option 1 \'97 Accept the inconsistency Document it clearly, handle gracefully in the viewer, move forward. The inconsistency is honest \'97 it reflects the pipeline's evolution. Most users won't notice or care.\
Option 2 \'97 Backfill missing fields Run a script that adds null values for missing fields to older city packs. This makes the schema consistent without re-running the pipelines. For example, add 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 "writer_profile": null
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  to all v3/v4 source entries, 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 "lat": null
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  to all Barcelona/Valencia restaurants, 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 "cuisine": null
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  to all Valencia restaurants. This is a 30-minute Claude Code task.\
Option 3 \'97 Re-run Valencia and Barcelona with v5 Produces genuinely richer data \'97 writer profiles, better cuisine tagging, coordinates. But takes 2 pipeline runs and significant time. Barcelona v4 is already strong with 52 restaurants and 14 both-pool entries \'97 a v5 re-run might not improve it much.\
\
My recommendation\
Option 2 first \'97 backfill missing fields with null values. This takes 30 minutes, makes the schema consistent for any code that processes the files, and eliminates potential viewer bugs from missing fields.\
Option 3 for Valencia specifically \'97 it's the only v3 city and has no cuisine data, no coordinates, and no source_type fields. A v5 re-run of Valencia would produce a meaningfully better pack. Worth doing when you're ready to run European cities.\
Barcelona is less urgent \'97 v4 is already strong and a v5 re-run is unlikely to add much beyond writer profiles and coordinates.\
Want to do the backfill now?\
