+61 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Toronto\
\ls296\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
La Grande Table Marocaine 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  wrong Marrakesh location\
\ls296\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Benyamna 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  wrong Moroccan location\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The v3 bounding box script now catches most of these automatically. But Chefchaouen achieved zero false positives partly because the medina is so geographically compact \'97 every restaurant is within 300 metres of every other restaurant. For a larger city like Lisbon or Copenhagen, a restaurant name that matches something in the wrong neighbourhood would still pass the bounding box check but be in the wrong location.\
A tighter per-neighbourhood bounding box would help but would require pre-populating neighbourhood coordinates for every city \'97 significant preparation work.\
\
The concentration cap inconsistency\
The cap fired differently across cities:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls297\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
