\cf2 For the proximity feature to work across all cities, Barcelona and Valencia need coordinates first. That's the geocoding pass we've been deferring.\
\
My honest assessment of the current map\
The current map is better than nothing \'97 it gives a spatial sense of where restaurants are clustered. But you're right that it doesn't solve the core traveller use case. A user standing in Gueliz doesn't want to tap around a map \'97 they want an immediate answer.\
Option 3 (neighbourhood-first) is the most practical near-term improvement because it works with existing data and no permissions. A prominent "I'm in..." selector on the city page would be genuinely useful today.\
Option 2 (near me list) is the highest-value feature but requires coordinates on all cities first.\
Option 1 (map with radius) is the most visually impressive but also the most complex and the least useful per unit of effort.\
\
What I'd suggest\
Add neighbourhood-first navigation now \'97 it works with existing data, is genuinely useful for travellers, and is a 2-3 hour build. Then do the Barcelona/Valencia coordinate enrichment pass, and add the "Near me" distance sort as the premium feature once all cities have coordinates.\
The map stays as a secondary view for spatial orientation \'97 useful for some users \'97 but neighbourhood-first navigation becomes the primary tool for the core use case.\
