\fs32 \cf2 My honest assessment\
If you were building LocalBite as a production product targeting thousands of users, I'd say stay with Leaflet for cost and independence reasons.\
But if the priority right now is getting a genuinely useful proximity feature working quickly so you can test it with friends and get real feedback \'97 Google Maps is the faster path. The $200 monthly credit means it's effectively free until you have significant traffic, at which point you'd have the revenue question to consider anyway.\
The terms of service issue is real but manageable \'97 switching from Leaflet tiles to Google Maps tiles is the main change required to be compliant.\
\
The question worth sitting with\
Is the proximity feature important enough to the core use case that you want to prioritise it and potentially switch map providers? Or is it a nice-to-have that can wait until after you've validated the product with real users?\
Given that you've already observed the current map doesn't fully solve the proximity use case, and given that the proximity feature is arguably the most genuinely useful thing a map can do for a traveller \'97 it might be worth making the switch now rather than building on Leaflet and rebuilding later.\
What's your instinct?\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
