\cf2 Yes \'97 that's exactly the right framing. Strip away all the other considerations and the decision is simply:\
2 hours on Google Maps versus 5.5 hours on Leaflet for the same feature.\
At this stage of the project \'97 pre-launch, testing with friends, validating the concept \'97 the 3.5 hour difference is meaningful. That's time better spent running more cities, building the near-me list view, or getting the Barcelona and Valencia coordinates done.\
The cost concern is theoretical at current scale. The terms of service concern is solved by switching map tiles. The vendor lock-in concern is a future problem that only matters if LocalBite succeeds.\
My recommendation: switch to Google Maps.\
To do it properly you'd need:\
