A Google Maps API key (free to set up, $200 monthly credit)\
\ls308\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Replace the Leaflet CSS/JS imports with the Google Maps SDK\
\ls308\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Rewrite the map initialisation and marker code \'97 roughly 100 lines\
\ls308\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Add the My Location button \'97 one line\
\ls308\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	5	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Handle the proximity message \'97 30 minutes\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The existing marker logic (teardrop pins for verified, dashed circles for approximate, green for both-pool) would need to be rebuilt using Google Maps markers but the logic itself doesn't change.\
Want to make the switch as part of the next session alongside adding the proximity feature?\
