\cf2 Good question to examine before we scale up to more cities. Here are the realistic alternatives worth considering:\
\
1. Photon (OpenStreetMap-based, free)\
Photon is a geocoding API built on OpenStreetMap data, developed by Komoot (the cycling/hiking app company). It's specifically designed for autocomplete and place search rather than batch geocoding.\
Advantages:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls310\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Completely free, no API key, no rate limits for reasonable use\
\ls310\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Same underlying OSM data as Nominatim but with a different search algorithm that often returns better results for partial or ambiguous names\
\ls310\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Supports bounding box queries natively \'97 same improvement we added to Nominatim v3\
\ls310\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Returns results in order of relevance rather than just geographic proximity\
\ls310\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Faster than Nominatim for many queries\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Disadvantages:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls311\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Same coverage gaps as Nominatim \'97 if a restaurant isn't in OpenStreetMap, Photon won't find it either\
\ls311\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Less battle-tested than Nominatim for production use\
\ls311\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
No guaranteed uptime SLA\
\ls311\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Documentation is thinner\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Verdict: Worth adding as a fallback after Nominatim. If Nominatim returns nothing within the bounding box, try Photon before going to manual lookup. Likely improves hit rate by 5-10% at zero cost.\
\
2. Pelias (OpenStreetMap + OpenAddresses, free self-hosted)\
Pelias is an open-source geocoding engine used by Mapzen (now part of Linux Foundation). It combines OSM data with OpenAddresses (a global open address database) and Who's On First (a gazetteer of places).\
Advantages:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls312\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
More data sources than Nominatim \'97 OpenAddresses fills gaps where OSM is weak\
\ls312\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Can be self-hosted for complete control\
\ls312\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Good bounding box support\
\ls312\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Used in production by serious mapping companies\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Disadvantages:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls313\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Self-hosting requires a server \'97 not free in that sense\
\ls313\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The hosted version (geocode.earth) costs $50/month minimum\
\ls313\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Significant setup complexity if self-hosting\
\ls313\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Overkill for LocalBite's current scale\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Verdict: Not appropriate now. Worth knowing about for when LocalBite scales to a full production product with its own server infrastructure.\
\
3. HERE Geocoding API (freemium)\
HERE is Nokia's mapping platform, a serious Google Maps competitor used by many automotive and logistics companies.\
Advantages:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls314\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
250,000 free geocoding requests per month \'97 far more than needed\
\ls314\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Excellent coverage in Europe, decent in Morocco\
\ls314\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Named place search (restaurant name + city) is specifically supported\
\ls314\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Returns structured address data and coordinates together\
\ls314\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
No terms of service restriction on displaying results outside HERE maps\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Disadvantages:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls315\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Requires account and API key setup\
\ls315\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Free tier has usage limits that could become relevant at scale\
\ls315\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Coverage in Moroccan medinas is better than Nominatim but not as good as Google Maps\
\ls315\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Less community knowledge and fewer code examples than Google or Nominatim\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Verdict: Genuinely worth considering as the primary geocoder for European cities where HERE has strong coverage. Better than Nominatim for city names, street addresses, and restaurant chains. Less clear advantage for small independent restaurants in medinas.\
\
4. Mapbox Geocoding API (freemium)\
Mapbox is a well-regarded mapping platform used by many consumer apps including Snapchat and The Weather Channel.\
Advantages:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls316\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
100,000 free requests per month\
\ls316\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Good forward geocoding (name 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  coordinates)\
\ls316\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Excellent documentation and code examples\
\ls316\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Returns confidence scores natively \'97 no need to build our own\
\ls316\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Supports proximity bias (bias results toward a location) which is cleaner than our bounding box approach\
\ls316\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
No restriction on displaying results outside Mapbox maps\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Disadvantages:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls317\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Requires account and API key\
\ls317\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Coverage in Morocco is moderate \'97 better than Nominatim in cities, similar in medinas\
\ls317\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Paid tiers start at $0.75 per 1,000 requests after free limit\
\ls317\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Slightly more complex API than Nominatim\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Verdict: Worth testing on a European city batch. The proximity bias feature is a cleaner version of what we built with bounding boxes. Free tier is generous enough for LocalBite's current and near-term scale.\
\
5. Overpass API (OpenStreetMap raw queries, free)\
Overpass is a query language for raw OpenStreetMap data. Instead of asking "where is Restaurant X" you ask "give me all amenity=restaurant nodes within this bounding box with name=X."\
Advantages:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls318\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Completely free, no API key\
\ls318\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Same data as Nominatim but with more powerful querying\
\ls318\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Can search by name AND amenity type AND bounding box simultaneously \'97 more precise than Nominatim\
\ls318\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Can return multiple nearby candidates for manual review\
\ls318\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Used by serious OSM developers\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Disadvantages:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls319\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
More complex query syntax \'97 not a simple REST call\
\ls319\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Slower than Nominatim for simple lookups\
\ls319\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Same coverage gaps \'97 if it's not in OSM, Overpass won't find it\
\ls319\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Requires writing Overpass QL queries rather than plain text\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Verdict: Worth adding as a third attempt after Nominatim and Photon fail. Overpass's ability to query by amenity type within a tight bounding box is specifically useful for the restaurant name matching problem we've been solving manually.\
