\fs32 \cf2 Two recommended test combinations\
\
Combination 1 \'97 Maximum free coverage, no new accounts\
Sequence: Nominatim 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Photon 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Overpass 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  manual\
Rationale: All three services use OpenStreetMap data but with different search algorithms and query approaches. Nominatim uses text search with address parsing. Photon uses a different relevance ranking algorithm that often succeeds where Nominatim fails on ambiguous or partial names. Overpass uses exact attribute matching (name=X AND amenity=restaurant within bounding box) which catches cases where the other two return wrong matches.\
Each successive service addresses a different failure mode:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls324\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Nominatim fails when: name is ambiguous, returns out-of-bounds result\
\ls324\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Photon succeeds when: Nominatim's relevance ranking picked the wrong match\
\ls324\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Overpass succeeds when: the restaurant is in OSM but Nominatim and Photon couldn't match the name \'97 Overpass's exact match within bbox finds it\
