Adding Overpass: +3-5% Morocco, +5-8% Europe \'97 estimated based on exact name matching within bbox\
\ls325\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Combined: ~58-65% Morocco, ~78-85% Europe\
\ls325\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Manual needed: ~35-42% Morocco, ~15-22% Europe\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 How to test: Run Lisbon with this combination. Compare against Chefchaouen's Nominatim-only 65% result to see if Photon and Overpass add meaningful value for a European city.\
Setup cost: 1 hour for Photon, 3 hours for Overpass. Total 4 hours. No new accounts or API keys.\
\
Combination 2 \'97 Best automated coverage for European batch runs\
Sequence: Nominatim 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Mapbox 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Photon 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  manual\
Rationale: Nominatim handles the easy cases (restaurants well-mapped in OSM). Mapbox handles the harder cases \'97 it has a larger proprietary dataset than pure OSM services and its proximity bias feature is cleaner than our bounding box approach for European cities where neighbourhood boundaries are less rigid. Photon as a third attempt catches any remaining OSM-indexed restaurants that Nominatim missed due to ranking issues.\
Mapbox is placed second rather than third because its non-OSM data sources are most likely to find restaurants that OSM doesn't have \'97 making it more complementary to Nominatim than Photon which draws from the same data pool.\
Expected hit rates:\
