\ls326\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Nominatim alone: ~65% Europe (estimated)\
\ls326\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Adding Mapbox: +10-15% Europe \'97 estimated based on proprietary dataset covering restaurants not in OSM\
\ls326\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Adding Photon: +3-5% Europe \'97 catches remaining OSM restaurants Nominatim missed\
\ls326\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Combined: ~78-85% Europe\
\ls326\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Manual needed: ~15-22% Europe\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 For Morocco specifically Mapbox's advantage over Nominatim is smaller \'97 the gap between OSM and proprietary data is less pronounced in medinas where neither dataset is strong.\
How to test: Run Lisbon with Combination 1 first, then run Porto with Combination 2. Compare hit rates between the two to assess whether Mapbox's proprietary data adds meaningful value over pure OSM services for Portuguese cities.\
Setup cost: Mapbox account + API key + 2-3 hours implementation. Photon already built from Combination 1. Total 3-4 additional hours after Combination 1 is implemented.\
