\cf2 Fair challenge \'97 I was not rigorous enough in that claim. Let me examine it honestly.\
\
What I actually said versus what I can support\
I claimed Combination 2 is "best for European batch runs" but the evidence for that is weak. The expected hit rates I gave for both combinations are 78-85% for Europe \'97 essentially identical. I don't have data showing Mapbox specifically outperforms Overpass for batch runs. The "best for batch runs" label was an assertion not a conclusion.\
\
What "batch run" actually requires from a geocoding service\
For a batch of 10 cities with 50 restaurants each \'97 500 requests total \'97 the relevant considerations are:\
Rate limits \'97 can the service handle 500 requests without throttling or blocking?\
