\fs32 \cf2 Revised recommendation for batch runs specifically\
If batch reliability matters \'97 meaning you want to run 10 cities overnight without babysitting it \'97 the argument for HERE or Mapbox is commercial uptime reliability, not hit rate. Community-run services like Nominatim and Photon are fine for manual runs where you're watching but carry more risk for unattended batch runs.\
For LocalBite at current scale this distinction doesn't matter much \'97 500 requests across 10 cities is trivial volume. The unattended reliability concern only becomes real when you're running 50+ cities in a single batch.\
\
Revised two combinations with honest rationale\
Combination 1 \'97 Best free option, good for all scales\
Nominatim 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Photon 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  manual\
Drop Overpass \'97 its batch suitability is poor due to query complexity and slowness under load. Photon alone adds meaningful value over Nominatim at zero cost and effort. Simple, fast, free, reliable enough for runs of up to 20 cities.\
Expected Europe hit rate: ~73-78%\
Expected Morocco hit rate: ~55-62%\
Setup cost: 1 hour\
Batch reliability: Moderate\
Combination 2 \'97 Best for reliable unattended batch runs of 20+ cities\
Nominatim 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  HERE 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Photon 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  manual\
HERE is placed second because its commercial reliability and proprietary dataset make it the most valuable addition to Nominatim for unattended runs. Photon third as a free catch-all for remaining OSM-indexed restaurants. The sequence prioritises reliability and coverage in that order.\
Expected Europe hit rate: ~80-87%\
Expected Morocco hit rate: ~62-70%\
Setup cost: 4-5 hours including HERE account\
Batch reliability: Excellent\
