There's no principled reason to limit it. The 22-query structure in v5 was a practical decision made during the Marrakesh run to balance thoroughness against rate limit consumption and run time. It's not a tested optimal number.\
For the apples-to-apples test the more important constraint is that both strategies should use the same number of searches, or the comparison should explicitly account for the difference. If Strategy A uses 22 queries and Strategy B uses 31, the right comparison metric is both-pool entries per query used, not raw both-pool count.\
Alternatively \'97 and this is probably cleaner \'97 run both strategies with the same total query budget (say 30 queries each) and see how each allocates those queries and what results they produce. Strategy A would use its standard angle distribution across 30 queries. Strategy B would front-load writer-first queries. Same total budget, different allocation.\
