\
Option 2 \'97 Estimate from known pricing\
On the API, Sonnet 4.6 is $3 per million input tokens and $15 per million output tokens. But on Claude Pro you're not paying per token \'97 you're consuming from a rate-limited quota. The token count still matters because it tells you how many cities you can run per session before hitting the limit.\
If Chefchaouen used 116.5k tokens in 21 minutes, and the Pro rate limit resets every 5 hours, a rough estimate is you could run approximately 4-5 cities per session on standard Sonnet before hitting the limit \'97 assuming similar token usage per city.\
For the test specifically, knowing that Strategy B uses 36 queries vs 30 gives us a rough expectation that Strategy B will consume approximately 20% more tokens than Strategy A, all else being equal. The actual token count will tell us if that's accurate.\
\
Option 3 \'97 Add token tracking to the pipeline prompt\
We could instruct the pipeline to report its estimated token usage at the end of the run. Claude Code can't measure its own tokens precisely but can estimate based on what it processed. More reliably, the completion banner always shows the actual count \'97 we just need to capture it before it scrolls away.\
\
