The combined approach \'97 Strategy C\
The insight is that the two strategies failed in complementary ways. Strategy A's weakness was missing independent critics. Strategy B's weakness was missing high-volume aggregator coverage. A combined approach would run both phases deliberately:\
Phase 0 \'97 Direct fetch of known high-quality independent sources (new) Before any searches, directly fetch 2-3 known high-quality independent critics for the city via Jina. For Lisbon this would be Mesa Marcada and Observador. For Porto it would be different critics identified during city variable preparation. This ensures independent voices are always in the pack regardless of whether searches surface them.\
This addresses the Test F question directly \'97 not as a replacement for searching but as a guaranteed floor of quality.\
Phase 1 \'97 Standard structured searches (30 queries) Keep Strategy A's full angle distribution intact \'97 don't reduce city-wide or neighbourhood queries to make room for writer-first. Run all 30 queries as in Strategy A.\
Phase 2 \'97 Writer-first supplementary searches (4-6 additional queries) After the main 30 queries, run 4-6 writer-first queries specifically targeting independent critics and journalists \'97 not as a replacement for standard angles but as a supplement. Use any writer names found in Phase 0 direct fetches to personalise these queries.\
Total: 3 direct fetches + 30 standard queries + 4-6 writer-first = 36-38 total actions\
This is comparable to Strategy B's 36 total but structured differently \'97 full standard coverage plus guaranteed independent source coverage rather than trading one for the other.\
Publisher-level concentration cap (new rule) Add a rule to the pipeline: if any single publisher contributes more than 2 articles to the source pool, flag it and require the diversity gate to be met by sources from at least 3 distinct publishers. This prevents Time Out PT dominating through article proliferation while still counting its articles toward both-pool.\
Conflict of interest check (new rule) Add an explicit check for commercial conflicts: does the publication operate a food venue, accept advertising from restaurants, or have a commercial relationship with the dining industry? Flag but don't auto-reject \'97 require disclosure in the writer profile. This would have surfaced the Time Out Market issue.\
