\fs32 \cf2 *Unreliable \'97 rate limit interruption\
The asterisk on Strategy A's 23 both-pool count is now critical. If we define both-pool strictly as independent editorial voices from different organisations \'97 which is what the LocalBite concept promises \'97 Strategy A's real both-pool count is likely 0-5, not 23.\
\
Recommendations\
1. Redefine the both-pool signal\
The current definition \'97 "restaurant recommended by sources from two different language pools" \'97 is too loose. It allows same-publisher cross-language editions to qualify. The definition should be tightened to: "restaurant recommended by two editorially independent organisations writing in different languages."\
Under this definition Time Out EN + Time Out PT does not qualify. Mesa Marcada + Culinary Backstreets would qualify if they name the same restaurant.\
2. Strategy C is the right methodology but needs a different quality metric\
Strategy C found the highest-quality sources of all three strategies \'97 genuinely independent critics with no commercial conflicts. The zero both-pool count is not a failure of the methodology; it's an honest reflection of what independent EN and PT critics actually recommend in Lisbon. The product should celebrate this rather than treating it as a weakness.\
3. The official Lisbon pack decision\
