\fs32 \cf2 \
The three headline conclusions from all three strategy runs:\
1. The both-pool signal is broken for same-publisher sources. Strategy A's 23 both-pool entries were largely Time Out EN + Time Out PT \'97 one publisher in two languages. Under a corrected independent-only definition, Strategy A's real both-pool count is likely near zero. This affects how we interpret all six existing city packs.\
2. Independent critics cover different restaurants. Strategy C confirmed that genuinely independent EN and PT critics in Lisbon recommend fundamentally different places \'97 EN writers favour neighbourhood character restaurants, PT critics favour fine dining. This is honest and valuable information, not a failure.\
3. No single strategy is right alone. Strategy A has breadth but inflated quality signals. Strategy C has source quality but limited coverage. The Lisbon pack should merge both with transparent source flagging.\
Once Strategy C export confirms, archive the files and we can move to geocoding.\
