\cf2 My recommendation is merge, but with a specific approach that's simpler than it sounds.\
\
The case for merging\
The three strategies found largely non-overlapping restaurants. Strategy A found 63 restaurants primarily through Time Out \'97 high-volume, tourist-facing, same-publisher cross-language. Strategy C found 36 restaurants through genuinely independent critics \'97 Mesa Marcada, Observador, Culinary Backstreets, Ola Daniela. These two sets represent different but equally valid perspectives on Lisbon's food scene.\
A traveller using LocalBite deserves both. The independent PT critic recommendations (Lamina, Y\uc0\u333 so, Henrique S\'e1 Pessoa) are genuinely valuable and would be invisible in a Strategy A-only pack. The Time Out volume (63 restaurants across all neighbourhoods) provides breadth that Strategy C alone can't match.\
\
The practical merge approach\
Rather than a complex programmatic merge, the simplest approach is:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls409\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Start with Strategy A's 63 restaurants as the base\
\ls409\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Add Strategy C restaurants not already in Strategy A \'97 approximately 20-25 unique entries\
\ls409\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Flag Time Out sources with 
\f1 \uc0\u9888 
\f0  coi in the JSON\
\ls409\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Apply the corrected both-pool definition \'97 Time Out EN + Time Out PT pairs are downgraded from both-pool to single-pool. Genuine both-pool only where an independent EN source and independent PT source name the same restaurant\
\ls409\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	5	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The resulting pack would have approximately 80-85 restaurants\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Expected both-pool count after correction: Looking at Strategy A's 23 "both-pool" entries \'97 most were Time Out EN + Time Out PT. Under the corrected definition these become single-pool entries. Any restaurant appearing in both a Strategy A source and a Strategy C source (e.g. Canalha appears in both \'97 it's in Strategy A via Time Out and in Strategy C via Culinary Backstreets) would qualify as genuine both-pool if the sources are independent.\
The corrected both-pool count will be lower than 23 but more honest. Possibly 5-10 genuine entries.\
\
The honest trade-off\
The merge is more work \'97 it requires a Claude Code task to deduplicate, apply corrected both-pool logic, and flag Time Out entries. Probably 20-30 minutes.\
The simpler option is Strategy C alone \'97 36 restaurants, all honest, all from independent sources with no COI. It's a thinner pack but a cleaner one. For a city like Lisbon with strong independent food writing, 36 restaurants is actually sufficient for a useful travel tool.\
\
My final recommendation: use Strategy C as the official pack, with a note in the research summary that a merge is possible\
The reason I'm recommending Strategy C alone despite arguing for the merge above is practical:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls410\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The test has already taken 3 full pipeline runs and significant analysis\
\ls410\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Strategy C's 36 restaurants are all genuinely high-quality recommendations\
\ls410\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The merge adds complexity and another 20-30 minutes for marginal improvement\
\ls410\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The corrected both-pool redefinition means Strategy A's apparent advantage largely disappears anyway\
\ls410\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Lisbon is not yet published \'97 it's going straight to geocoding and then the viewer. Users will not notice the difference between 36 and 85 restaurants if the 36 are excellent\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 The merge makes sense as a future improvement pass once the both-pool redefinition is properly implemented across all cities. Doing it now on Lisbon alone before the methodology is settled would create an inconsistent city pack.\
Use Strategy C. Geocode it. Ship it. Come back to the merge question when the both-pool redefinition is applied consistently across all city packs.\
