\fs32 \cf2 What high and medium confidence mean\
These ratings are assigned by the script based on what type of result the geocoding service returned \'97 not a score the service itself provides.\
High confidence means the service returned a result whose type strongly suggests it found the actual business:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls435\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Nominatim: result has 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 class = amenity
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  \'97 meaning OSM has this specifically tagged as a food/drink venue\
\ls435\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
HERE: result has 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 resultType = place
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  \'97 meaning HERE's database has a named place entry for it\
\ls435\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Photon: result has 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 type
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  matching restaurant, cafe, bar, or fast_food\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Medium confidence means the service returned something in the right area but the match type is weaker:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls436\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Nominatim: result is in bounds but not tagged as amenity \'97 could be a street, building, or area\
\ls436\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
HERE: result is in bounds but 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 resultType
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  is street, area, or address rather than a named place\
\ls436\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Photon: result is in bounds but not tagged as a food venue\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
