\cf2 Yes \'97 this is exactly the right question to ask before proceeding. The confidence ratings are telling us something important that we haven't fully acted on yet.\
\
What the ratings reveal about our current process\
The confidence rating is assigned at geocoding time based on result type. But we're currently treating all results the same \'97 they all go into the JSON and all get plotted on the map. A "Rua de Alc\'e2ntara" street result for Y\uc0\u333 so gets the same treatment as a confirmed "O Primo do Queijo" place result.\
This means the viewer is silently showing potentially wrong pins with no indication of reliability. A user tapping Y\uc0\u333 so's pin could walk to the wrong location.\
\
What the ratings suggest for our process\
There are three places in the workflow where confidence ratings could do real work:\
1 \'97 At geocoding time (script level)\
Rather than accepting all results equally, the script could apply different acceptance thresholds per service and confidence level:\
