\cf2 Good \'97 let's think this through from the user's perspective before touching the script.\
\
What the user experiences today\
The viewer shows all restaurant pins identically on the map. Every pin looks the same regardless of whether the coordinate came from a confirmed Nominatim exact match ("O Primo do Queijo") or a HERE street-level guess ("Rua de Alc\'e2ntara" for Y\uc0\u333 so). The user has no way to know which pins are trustworthy and which might send them to the wrong location.\
For a travel tool this is a meaningful problem. If someone is walking in Alc\'e2ntara looking for Y\uc0\u333 so and taps the pin, they could end up at a random point on Rua de Alc\'e2ntara rather than the actual restaurant. That's a bad experience that damages trust in the whole product.\
\
Three possible approaches for the map view\
Option A \'97 Hide uncertain pins entirely\
Only plot restaurants with high-confidence coordinates. Medium-confidence and unverified restaurants appear in the card list but have no pin on the map. The card would show a small "location unverified" note instead of a map link.\
Pros: Map is 100% trustworthy \'97 every pin is correct\
Cons: Some restaurants invisible on map \'97 feels incomplete, user might not understand why\
Option B \'97 Show all pins but visually distinguish confidence\
Plot all restaurants but use different pin styles:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
