\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 0.0001
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  is a numeric confidence score that the old Nominatim v1/v2 script wrote directly from Nominatim's API response. Nominatim returns a field called 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 importance
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  \'97 a float between 0 and 1 that reflects how prominent the place is in OpenStreetMap's database. A famous landmark might score 0.8. A small local restaurant with minimal OSM data might score 0.0001.\
The old script was passing this raw 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 importance
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  value through directly into 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 geo_confidence
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  instead of converting it to a meaningful label. So 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 0.0001
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  doesn't mean "very low confidence in the coordinate" \'97 it means "this place has very low prominence in OSM" which is a different thing entirely. A restaurant with 0.0001 importance could still have a perfectly correct coordinate \'97 it just means OSM doesn't have much data about it beyond its location.\
The practical implication:\
The 5 Rabat restaurants and 2 each in Fes and Marrakesh with 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 0.0001
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  are probably correctly located \'97 Nominatim found them and returned coordinates within the bounding box. The low importance score just means they're small local establishments with minimal OSM metadata, not that the pin is in the wrong place.\
This means treating 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 0.0001
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  the same as 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 medium
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  in the viewer \'97 showing a hollow pin \'97 may actually be slightly unfair to those restaurants. Their coordinates are likely correct; it's just that OSM doesn't know much about them beyond where they are.\
The honest options:\
One option is to treat 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 0.0001
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  as 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 high
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  since the coordinate itself is likely correct. Another is to keep it as hollow since we can't be certain without manual verification.\
My recommendation is to treat 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 0.0001
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  as 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 medium
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  \'97 hollow pin \'97 for now, with a note that these should be manually verified when we geocode Morocco cities properly with the v5 script. The hollow pin is a conservative but honest choice given we can't verify from here.\
Does that make sense before we proceed?\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
