\cf2 Yes \'97 almost certainly.\
Google Maps Terms of Service prohibit automated scraping of their platform. Using Claude Code to programmatically fetch coordinates from Google Maps \'97 whether by scraping the website or calling the Maps API without proper authentication and billing setup \'97 would violate those terms.\
There are three specific issues:\
1 \'97 Scraping Google Maps UI is prohibited Google's Terms of Service explicitly forbid extracting data from Google Maps by automated means without their permission. Claude Code fetching Google Maps pages to extract coordinates would be scraping.\
2 \'97 Google Maps API requires a key and billing The legitimate way to get coordinates programmatically from Google is the Google Maps Geocoding API \'97 which requires an API key, a billing account, and costs $5 per 1,000 requests. Using it without those in place violates the terms.\
3 \'97 Storing coordinates derived from Google Maps may be restricted Even with a proper API key, Google's terms restrict how you can store and use geocoding results. You can cache them temporarily but permanent storage in a database or JSON file for use outside Google's ecosystem is restricted under standard terms.\
What we're doing instead is correct:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls460\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Nominatim \'97 OpenStreetMap data, open license, explicitly permits storing results\
\ls460\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
HERE \'97 commercial API with terms we agreed to, free tier permits our use case\
\ls460\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Manual lookup on Google Maps \'97 you reading the coordinates yourself and typing them in is not automated scraping. That's just a human using a website normally.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 So the manual lookup approach is not only more accurate \'97 it's also the legally clean way to handle the cases that automated geocoding can't resolve.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
