\cf2 Good \'97 let me think through this carefully and honestly before we lock in a standard.\
\
What we actually tested\
We tested Nominatim alone and Nominatim + HERE v6 on one city (Lisbon, 36 restaurants). We did not run a proper Combination 1 test because Photon produced too many false positives before the name similarity check was added. So our comparison is:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls468\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Nominatim alone: 21/36 (58%) automated\
\ls468\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Nominatim + HERE: 33/36 (92%) automated before manual, 36/36 after 6 manual lookups\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 This is a meaningful result but it has limitations worth acknowledging.\
\
What we didn't test \'97 the honest gaps\
1. We never ran a clean Combination 1 (Nominatim + Photon with name similarity)\
Photon was dismissed after it produced false positives in the run before the name similarity check was added. But the name similarity check was specifically designed to fix that problem. We never actually ran Photon with the fix in place. It's possible Photon + name similarity check performs comparably to HERE for European cities \'97 both pull from OSM data ultimately, though via different algorithms.\
The fair test would be: reset Lisbon coordinates, run v6 Combination 1 (Nominatim 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Photon 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  manual), compare against Combination 2. We skipped this.\
2. One city is not enough to establish a standard\
Lisbon has excellent OSM coverage and a strong English-speaking expat community that contributes to OpenStreetMap. HERE also has strong Portugal coverage. A different city \'97 Fes, Chefchaouen, or a future city in a less well-mapped country \'97 might show a very different pattern. Our 8 percentage point threshold was based on Lisbon specifically.\
3. We don't know HERE's actual false positive rate after name similarity\
The name similarity check rejected 5 false positives from HERE. But Caf\'e9 des \'c9pices slipped through because "Caf\'e9" matched "Via Caf\'e9." We don't know how many other false positives might exist for cities with more ambiguous restaurant names \'97 Arabic names, names with common words like "casa", "maison", "beit".\
4. HERE's terms of service on data storage\
We noted Google Maps prohibits storing geocoding results. We accepted HERE's terms implicitly when signing up, but we didn't explicitly verify whether HERE's free tier permits permanent storage of geocoding results in a public GitHub repository. This is worth checking. OpenStreetMap/Nominatim explicitly permits this. HERE's terms may be more restrictive.\
5. API key dependency and fragility\
Nominatim requires no key and will never break due to authentication. HERE requires a key that can expire, be revoked, or change pricing. The v6 script gracefully falls back to manual if HERE fails, but it's worth acknowledging this dependency. For a hobby project this is low risk. For a production tool it matters more.\
6. We haven't tested Combination 2 on a non-European city\
Lisbon is a well-mapped European city. HERE's proprietary data advantage may be smaller for Moroccan cities where OSM coverage is weaker and HERE may also have limited data. The 33% improvement HERE provided for Lisbon may not replicate for Fes or Chefchaouen.\
\
Other geocoding options we didn't consider\
OpenCage \'97 wraps multiple sources including OSM, was our original Plan B when HERE setup was difficult. 2,500 free requests/day, simple API key, permissive storage terms. Worth considering as an alternative to HERE especially for non-European cities where HERE's proprietary data advantage may be smaller.\
Mapbox \'97 100,000 free requests/month, excellent global coverage, strong name matching. However storage terms are restrictive \'97 results cannot be permanently stored outside Mapbox's ecosystem without an enterprise licence. This disqualifies it for LocalBite.\
TomTom \'97 2,500 free requests/day, good European coverage, permissive terms. Not evaluated at all.\
Overpass API \'97 direct OSM query tool, more powerful than Nominatim for complex searches, can search by amenity type within a bounding box. Free, no key, permissive terms. Could find restaurants that Nominatim misses by querying OSM directly for 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 amenity=restaurant
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  within the city bounding box. We never considered this.\
Address-first approach \'97 instead of searching by restaurant name, search for the restaurant's street address if we can extract it from the source articles. This bypasses the name matching problem entirely. More work to implement but potentially higher accuracy.\
\
My honest assessment\
The Nominatim + HERE combination is good but not definitively proven as the best option for LocalBite. What we know confidently:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls469\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
HERE adds meaningful value over Nominatim alone for Lisbon (33 percentage points raw, ~31 quality-adjusted)\
\ls469\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
The name similarity check is essential \'97 without it HERE produces too many false positives\
\ls469\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Photon was unfairly dismissed \'97 it deserves a clean test with the name similarity check\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 What I'd recommend before locking in the standard:\
Short term \'97 one additional test: Run Combination 1 properly (Nominatim + Photon + name similarity) on Lisbon with the v6 script. This takes 5 minutes and directly answers whether we need HERE at all. If Photon performs within 8 percentage points of HERE, the free no-dependency option is preferable.\
Medium term \'97 verify HERE's storage terms: Confirm HERE's free tier permits storing geocoding results in a public GitHub repository. If it doesn't, we need to switch to OpenCage or TomTom.\
Longer term \'97 test on a non-European city: Run Combination 2 on Fes or Marrakesh before declaring it the standard for all cities. Morocco may behave very differently.\
\
