\fs32 \cf2 The decision is now clear and properly evidenced:\
Combination 2 (Nominatim + HERE) saves 11 human lookups per city versus Combination 1 \'97 well above the 3-lookup threshold we set. The name similarity check makes HERE reliable. Photon is genuinely weaker than HERE for restaurant name matching even with the similarity check \'97 it adds only 5 restaurants vs HERE's 12, and still generates 14 rejected false positives requiring processing time.\
However \'97 three caveats to document honestly:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls470\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
