\fs32 \cf2 This is a striking reversal. HERE dramatically outperforms Photon for European cities but dramatically underperforms for Morocco. The pattern is almost certainly geographic \'97 HERE has rich proprietary restaurant data for Europe but much weaker coverage for North Africa and the Middle East.\
\
This fundamentally changes the standard we should adopt\
A single global standard (always use HERE, or always use Photon) is wrong. The right approach is city-aware:\
European cities (Lisbon, Porto, Barcelona, Valencia, Copenhagen, etc.): 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Combination 2: Nominatim 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  HERE 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  manual\
North African and Middle Eastern cities (Marrakesh, Fes, Rabat, Chefchaouen, etc.): 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Combination 1: Nominatim 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  Photon 
\f2 \uc0\u8594 
\f0  manual\
This is easy to implement in the script \'97 add a 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 COMBINATION_OVERRIDE
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  map by city that forces the combination regardless of whether a HERE key is passed:\
\
