\cf2 No \'97 we don't know that with confidence. That was an assumption I made too quickly. Let me be honest about what we actually know and don't know.\
\
What we actually know:\
HERE returned results for all 8 Marrakesh queries \'97 the log says "no result in bounding box" not "no results found." This means HERE did return something for every query, but every result fell outside lat 31.4\'9631.8, lng -8.2\'96-7.8.\
That's a crucial distinction. The problem could be any of:\
1 \'97 HERE's data for Morocco is sparse or wrong Possible but unproven. We have no evidence of what HERE actually returned for those queries.\
2 \'97 The city centre bias (
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 &at=lat,lng
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1 ) is wrong for Marrakesh The script uses the midpoint of the bounding box as the centre bias. For Marrakesh that's approximately lat 31.6, lng -8.0. If HERE is interpreting that centre point differently or biasing toward a different Marrakesh \'97 there is another Marrakech in Algeria for example \'97 the results could land outside the bounding box consistently.\
3 \'97 The queries themselves are returning a different city "Sahbi Sahbi Marrakesh" might be returning a result in a different country if HERE's index prioritises differently than Nominatim.\
4 \'97 HERE requires the country name spelled differently HERE may index Morocco as "Maroc" (French) or "
\f10 \'c7\'e1\'e3\'db\'d1\'c8
\f0 " (Arabic) rather than "Morocco" \'97 causing the city+country combination in the query to fail to match.\
5 \'97 HERE's bounding box validation is working against us In the v6 script HERE results are validated against the bounding box after retrieval. If HERE returns coordinates in a slightly different format or projection, they might consistently fail the bounding box check even when the location is correct.\
\
What we should do before concluding\
The honest diagnostic is to see what HERE actually returned. Add a debug line to the script that prints the raw HERE response for each failed query, then run Marrakesh again. That would tell us immediately whether:\
