\cf2 HERE was delivering a genuine 20 percentage point improvement over Photon for European cities. The question is whether OpenCage, LocationIQ, or Geoapify can replicate that improvement \'97 or get close to it \'97 while being legally compliant.\
The reason to expect they might is that all three supplement OSM data with additional sources. OpenCage uses multiple geocoding systems including Nominatim, Data Science Toolkit, GeoPlanet, GeoNames, and more.
