\fs32 \cf2 For European restaurants that are in business directories and review platforms but not yet in OSM, these additional sources could find what Photon misses \'97 which is exactly what HERE was doing.\
The reason to be cautious is that HERE's proprietary restaurant data for Europe is genuinely deep \'97 it includes commercial POI databases that open-data services don't have access to. OpenCage, LocationIQ, and Geoapify all ultimately rely on open data sources, so their ceiling may be similar to Photon's rather than HERE's.\
\
