Option 1 \'97 Test OpenCage on Lisbon now Run Combination 1 vs OpenCage on Lisbon. Takes 10-15 minutes. Directly answers whether OpenCage closes the gap with HERE for European cities. If it does, we have a legal, compliant replacement. If it doesn't, we accept Nominatim + Photon as our European standard and absorb the extra manual lookups.\
Option 2 \'97 Accept Nominatim + Photon as standard now Skip further testing. Accept 10 manual lookups per European city (vs HERE's 3). For a hobby project running perhaps 10 European cities total, that's 70 extra manual lookups over the life of the project \'97 roughly 2-3 hours of extra work. Not catastrophic, and it eliminates all API key dependencies and legal risk.\
Option 3 \'97 Use LocationIQ specifically LocationIQ's free tier explicitly permits commercial use with attribution, has the highest free request limit (5,000/day), and is API-compatible with Nominatim. It's the lowest-friction commercial option to test.\
My recommendation is Option 1 with OpenCage \'97 it's the most established of the three alternatives with the clearest storage terms, and 10-15 minutes to test is worth it given the 20 percentage point gap we're trying to close. Shall I proceed with setting up the OpenCage test?\
