\fs32 \cf2 This is a meaningful distinction. "Store response data forever" refers to the coordinate values themselves. "Cache for 48 hours" on the free plan refers to storing request-response pairs to avoid re-querying. For LocalBite's use case \'97 storing coordinates in a public JSON file permanently \'97 the free plan's 48-hour cache limit is a problem. On a paid plan the storage is permitted for the duration of the subscription, but ceases to be permitted if you cancel. OpenCage explicitly permits permanent storage even after cancellation.\
