\fs32 \cf2 \
What this means for LocalBite specifically:\
LocationIQ draws a clear distinction between two things:\
Storing output \'97 the coordinate values (lat/lng) extracted from the API response. This is permitted forever on all plans including free.\
Caching \'97 storing the full request-response pair to avoid re-querying the API. This is limited to 48 hours on the free plan.\
For LocalBite we are storing coordinate values in a JSON file \'97 not caching request-response pairs. We extract 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 lat
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  and 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 lng
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  from the response and store only those values. We never intend to replay the cached response to avoid hitting the API again.\
Conclusion: LocationIQ's free tier permits what LocalBite does.\
Storing coordinate values permanently in a public GitHub JSON file is explicitly allowed under "store the output forever." The 48-hour caching restriction applies only to storing full request-response pairs, which LocalBite does not do.\
