\fs32 \cf2 The honest conclusion for LocalBite:\
The additional sources LocationIQ uses beyond OSM \'97 OpenAddresses, GeoNames, Who's On First \'97 are all open address and place name datasets, not commercial POI databases. None of them are equivalent to HERE's proprietary restaurant POI data, which is what gave HERE its 20 percentage point advantage over Photon for Lisbon.\
This means LocationIQ will almost certainly perform similarly to Photon for restaurant name matching in both European and Moroccan cities. The additional sources improve street address and administrative boundary data but are unlikely to find restaurants that Photon misses.\
