\fs32 \cf2 That sounds promising \'97 but the source of that data matters.\
Foursquare's POI database is built primarily from user check-ins and crowdsourced contributions. In the US, where Foursquare has dense check-in history, this produces excellent restaurant coverage. In Europe it is considerably weaker \'97 European users historically used Foursquare much less than American users, and the database reflects this. The restaurants that LocalBite targets \'97 independent, critic-recommended establishments that may have opened in 2024 or 2025 \'97 are precisely the type that have low check-in density and may not appear in Foursquare's database at all, even if they appear in OSM.\
The script we ran against Marrakesh confirmed this pattern \'97 Foursquare found zero restaurants in earlier versions of the geocoding script. European independent restaurants are unlikely to perform better.\
Even if Foursquare did find some restaurants, the storage prohibition would disqualify it. So it fails on both counts \'97 data coverage for European independent restaurants and storage terms.\
