\fs32 \cf2 This is not coincidental. These companies monetise their POI databases as a competitive asset. Permanent storage would allow competitors to build equivalent databases from their data \'97 which is precisely what their terms prohibit. The restriction is structural to the commercial model, not an oversight.\
