Now I have enough. Here is the complete assessment of national mapping agency APIs:\
\
IGN France (Institut National de l'Information G\'e9ographique et Foresti\'e8re)\
IGN's G\'e9oplateforme geocoding service draws from three data sources: the Base Adresse Nationale (BAN) updated weekly, a Points d'Int\'e9r\'eat (POI) layer from BD TOPO updated quarterly, and cadastral parcels updated quarterly.
\fs24 \cf4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://geoservices.ign.fr/documentation/services/services-geoplateforme/geocodage"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb27 IGN\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf28 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 The POI layer from BD TOPO is the relevant one for LocalBite \'97 it includes named places and points of interest. This is genuinely interesting \'97 BD TOPO is France's official topographic database maintained by the state, and it includes restaurant-level POI data updated quarterly. It is free, open data, and the API requires no key for basic use.\
However four important limitations apply for LocalBite:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls486\ilvl0\cf2 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
France only \'97 BD TOPO covers Metropolitan France and overseas territories. Zero value for Lisbon, Barcelona, Marrakesh, or any non-French city\
\ls486\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Address-first not name-first \'97 the BAN index is optimised for address geocoding, not restaurant name search. BD TOPO POI search by name is supported but not its primary function\
\ls486\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Storage terms \'97 as a French government open data service under Licence Ouverte/Open Licence 2.0, results can be stored permanently and used freely. No restrictions\
\ls486\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
POI coverage gap \'97 BD TOPO's restaurant coverage is good for established venues but likely weak for newer independent restaurants that LocalBite targets\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 Verdict for LocalBite: Useful only if LocalBite adds French cities. When that happens, IGN's G\'e9oplateforme should be tested as a Combination 3 option \'97 it may outperform Nominatim for French restaurant names. Not relevant to current cities.\
\
Instituto Geogr\'e1fico Nacional Spain (IGN Spain / CartoCiudad)\
Spain's national mapping agency offers a geocoding API via CartoCiudad. Free, open, permanent storage permitted under CC BY 4.0. However CartoCiudad is address-focused \'97 it geocodes street addresses not named POIs. No restaurant name search capability. Not relevant.\
\
DGT Portugal (Dire\'e7\'e3o-Geral do Territ\'f3rio)\
Portugal has a national address database (CAOP) but no public-facing geocoding API equivalent to IGN France or CartoCiudad Spain. Portuguese address data flows into OpenStreetMap via community contributors rather than through a dedicated API. Not relevant.\
\
Morocco national mapping agency (ANCFCC)\
Morocco's national land agency does not offer a public geocoding API. No relevant service exists. Not relevant.\
\
Final assessment \'97 are national mapping agencies worth adding to the table?\
For LocalBite's current cities (Lisbon, Morocco, Barcelona, Valencia): No \'97 none of the relevant national agencies offer useful restaurant-name geocoding APIs for these cities.\
For future French cities (Paris, Lyon, Bordeaux, Marseille): Yes \'97 IGN France's BD TOPO POI layer is worth testing. It is free, storage-permitted, and may outperform Nominatim for French restaurant names given it is France's official topographic database updated from authoritative sources.\
\
