\fs32 \cf2 The consistent pattern across all countries:\
Every national mapping agency in Western Europe follows the same model: they publish authoritative address data and geographic names, but not commercial restaurant POI databases. The reasons are structural \'97 national mapping agencies are mandated to document the built environment (addresses, roads, boundaries, administrative areas), not to maintain business directories. Restaurant POI data falls under commercial publishing, not national geodetic responsibility.\
The single exception that breaks this pattern \'97 and the reason IGN France was worth flagging previously \'97 is France's BD TOPO layer, which happens to include a POI layer covering named places of interest including restaurants. This is unusual among European national mapping agencies and reflects IGN's broader mandate to document France's topographic reality in detail.\
The only national agency addition to the LocalBite geocoding toolkit is therefore confirmed as IGN France, and only for French cities. Every other agency assessed provides address and place name data that duplicates what Nominatim already accesses via OSM imports, with no restaurant name discovery benefit.\
