What Overpass API actually is\
Overpass is fundamentally different from Nominatim and Photon in its purpose. Overpass is a read-only API optimised for data consumers who need to retrieve custom selected parts of OSM map data by search criteria such as location, type of objects, tag properties, or proximity.
\fs24 \cf4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Overpass_API"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \cb27 OpenStreetMap\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf28 \
}}\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\fs32 \cf2 It is not a geocoding service \'97 it is a database query engine over the full OSM dataset.\
The distinction matters for LocalBite. Nominatim and Photon answer "where is restaurant X?" \'97 you give them a name and get coordinates back. Overpass answers "what restaurants are in this bounding box?" \'97 you give it a geographic filter and get all matching OSM objects back. For LocalBite's use case, a query like 
\fs28\fsmilli14400 \cf7 \cb8 node[amenity=restaurant][name~"Broto",i](bbox)
\fs32 \cf2 \cb1  would return the node for Broto if and only if OSM contains it with that exact or fuzzy-matched name.\
