\fs32 \cf2 \'97 so there is no volume discount. You are paying exactly proportionally for exactly proportionally more usage. No economic efficiency gain.\
The value proposition is entirely:\
1. Flow preservation \'97 a pipeline that takes 20 minutes runs to completion instead of dying at minute 2 and requiring a restart. The restart itself costs time, mental overhead, and in your case tonight, cleanup work (deleting partial files).\
2. Predictability \'97 you can sit down to run a city pack and know it will finish, rather than gambling on whether you'll hit the limit mid-run.\
3. Time of day flexibility \'97 on Pro you're now forced to wait until midnight Toronto time to retry. On Max 5x you could have just re-run it immediately.\
The honest framing is: if you run roughly one full city pipeline per month, Pro is probably sufficient if you're willing to work around the reset window and run at off-peak times. If you're planning to run Toronto plus eventually geocode Barcelona and Valencia plus future cities, and you want to do that work when you feel like it rather than scheduling around midnight resets, Max 5x is worth it as a quality-of-life purchase rather than an economic one.\
If the real issue is oversized sessions and heavy usage comes in bursts rather than every day, Pro plus capped extra usage can be cheaper and cleaner than living on Max year-round.
