\cf2 The "dim rather than disappear" decision is important for the proxy test \'97 in a thin pack like Marrakesh (14 restaurants) or Rabat (10 restaurants), disappearing restaurants would frequently leave the user looking at an empty map. Dimming keeps context visible and invites the user to expand the radius.\
\
One pre-condition before building\
Barcelona and Valencia have zero coordinates currently. Before proximity is meaningful for those cities, they need geocoding. The viewer already gracefully handles missing coordinates by falling back to neighbourhood centroids \'97 but centroid-based proximity is misleading (it would show all "Gr\'e0cia" restaurants at the same point regardless of where in Gr\'e0cia they actually are). Worth noting as a dependency: proximity is only as good as the coordinate coverage underneath it.\
